name: Billie Bonck
text:
I called the store asked for fresh chicken, I was told they had plenty and I didn’t need to call to order. The lady on the phone assured me they had chicken, then she preceded to tell me it would be 20-25 minutes for fresh chicken. I drove to the store to find NO chicken! I asked why when I’d just called?  She the deli manager who had came in on her off day said and I quote it hasn’t been 25 minutes. After talking with Tim the person who was in charge, he took me into a small office to give me the managers phone number and told me he was trying to get me away from her so she’d shut up.
Once I walked to the exit door she said something loud enough for me to hear, I asked her if she had something to say I was right there to say it to my face, not as I was leaving. She then threatened to call the police.
I’ve never in my entire life been treated so rudely by a person in customer service. I’ve been in customer service for more than 25 years and wouldn’t hire this woman to take out my trash!!  Obviously she was not happy about being called into do her job therefore it showed in the way she treated me.
I sent my husband to the store just to verify what type of customer service I’d received.  He also noticed the negative attitude from the lady and the fact that the person in charge wasn’t taking responsibility for his coworkers actions.  We’re locals and stop by there quite often to purchase boat gas and chicken. I highly suggest this person be retrained with the way she speaks to her customers. Without customers she wouldn’t have a job!

name: Billie Bonck
text:
I called the store asked for fresh chicken, I was told they had plenty and I didn’t need to call to order. The lady on the phone assured me they had chicken, then she preceded to tell me it would be 20-25 minutes for fresh chicken. I drove to the store to find NO chicken! I asked why when I’d just called?  She the deli manager who had came in on her off day said and I quote it hasn’t been 25 minutes. After talking with Tim the person who was in charge, he took me into a small office to give me the managers phone number and told me he was trying to get me away from her so she’d shut up.
Once I walked to the exit door she said something loud enough for me to hear, I asked her if she had something to say I was right there to say it to my face, not as I was leaving. She then threatened to call the police.
I’ve never in my entire life been treated so rudely by a person in customer service. I’ve been in customer service for more than 25 years and wouldn’t hire this woman to take out my trash!!  Obviously she was not happy about being called into do her job therefore it showed in the way she treated me.
I sent my husband to the store just to verify what type of customer service I’d received.  He also noticed the negative attitude from the lady and the fact that the person in charge wasn’t taking responsibility for his coworkers actions.  We’re locals and stop by there quite often to purchase boat gas and chicken. I highly suggest this person be retrained with the way she speaks to her customers. Without customers she wouldn’t have a job!

name: J Paul
text: Mr Anderson, I am the cashier that waited on your wife that morning. First of all, I need you to understand I wasn’t ignoring her. You forgot to mention the customer that I was talking with when you pulled up. The conversation we were having was work related, and you forgot to mention your wife waited less than a minute for me to take care of her. You also forgot to mention that your wife was trying to shut you up when you came in yelling and cursing at me. You also forgot to mention when you were cursing at me all I said to you was sir please leave the store. Not that it’s your business but I chose 3rd shift. My customers are my number one priority. I take my job very serious when it comes to my customers. I don’t like  that you’re unhappy,but I also know everyone can’t be pleased. I know you said your wife was disabled... maybe you should try getting out for her next time if 1 minute is too much time for her to be up.  You sure were able to get out to cuss me out. I don’t like that you’re unhappy with me, but I’ve done nothing wrong. Don’t know what else to say. Have a great day and “Take it easy”.

text: Totally renovated. This is now a Circle K and the staff from the manager Ron to the cashiers are always friendly and have a smile. Only complaint is that they have more problems than they should with their soda machines. They are brand new but they seem to be down once a week and that is disappointing. Other than that, very happy!

resp.text: Hello Ben, thank you for your feedback and for choosing our store. We have shared your note with our management team. Thanks.

name: Audra Kennedy
text: I normally go in there several times a week. That stops today. I asked on several times for them to order my husband dip. So that they would have extra for other people. I go in there this morning to purchase four rolls of dip and there is more than enough on the shelf to have a couple cans left. Cashier refuses to sell me four rolls. She says that she needs to have them INCASE someone else wants to purchase them.   Tell me why would you refuse to sale any items in a store that is there to be sold in the first place. We have six tobacco users in my home. And three of the members are guys so they dip and smoke. I promise you that you may not miss one sale but the couple of hundreds of dollars we spend a week is gone. I was understanding the many times I have gone in and they didn’t have enough there. But I asked them to please order so many cans for my hubby and we would buy them every other week. He is a OTR driver and preferred to give his money to the town we live in

resp.text: Hi there, thank you for letting us know and we are sorry about your experience. We have passed on your message to our local management team.

All my wife wanted was a pack of cigarettes. As we pulled up to the store, we noticed that the woman working at the time was  outside smoking. My wife went inside and the clerk made no attempt to go inside and attend to the customer that just walked through the door. My wife says that this woman is always working at this time and i suppose its because management does not want her interacting with too many people. I would urge everyone to stay away from this store but if you just have to go there, dont go at 3am

This is a picture of Ali.

name: Maggie Pinto
text: My boyfriend and I stopped here on our way to Texas in early January. We moved here from Maryland. Anyway, I left my wallet in the bathroom at this gas station. The station attendant, Ali, called me (I have my business cards in my wallet) and told me he had my wallet but since we were really far away at that point, I asked if he would mail it to me. He brought my wallet with him to college in Boston and kept it safe till last month then texted me when he was back home in Alabama and he mailed it to me. I just got it. text: My husband has a prescription he must have and Walgreens in Leeds Al. has this prescription. The drive through was closed today so I entered the store (not wanted to go inside trying to keep my husband as well as I can) the cashier, when I asked,  told me the pharmacy  was closed I asked to speak with the manager. The shift manager  can out and I asked him why the pharmacy  was closed he said someone  in the pharmacy tested positive  for COVID-19.  I told him I must have my husband's  prescription because  he could end up in the hospital  without it. His answer  was that he didn't  know when the pharmacy  would open back up and they were having the store cleaned  tonight by a professional cleaning  co. So what is a person to do if they depend  on a medication that they have a prescription for and can't  get it from the co. they have trusted to fill that prescription? The shift manager at 4:10 PM Tuesday  answer  was to call the doctor and get a new prescription sent to another store. I guess he doesn't  realize how difficult  it is to get intouch  with a doctor and a doctor at that time of day. Wouldn't  you think that the owner of this pathetic excuse  for a pharmacy would have had an emergency  plan in plan? We have been dealing with this Virus  for many months and a company this large should have a disaster plan in plan for just this type  of scenario. Pathetic. Everyone of my friends  has had a horrible  experience  with this store. We are going to flood the social media sources and expose  this company for who they are. They care nothing about the people  that keep them in business it's  all about money to this owner. Would you not think that they would close the whole store if someone  tested positive for COVID-19 I mean do they think that the virus decides to stay in one area of the store. Do they think that people  don't  go in there and touch products  before they go to the pharmacy. Just an example the bottom  line is money not care. Even Sonic  hamburger restaurant in Leeds Al. closed completely when one of it's employees tested positive and they sell burgers. The Walgreens in Leeds Al. Is absolutely  the worst pharmacy  in Leeds. You would think if they cared they would have had a disaster plan in place and they could have contacted all patrons that have life sustaining medications of the situation and where they could pick up their medication. There are many other drug stores  in Leeds and the surrounding area. I encourage  everyone who has had a dangerous experience with this co.to stop using  them and contact the head office. Good luck finding a competent person that works with this co. If I was a pharmacist  I would not want my name and reputation affiliated with Walgreens.

text:
I highly recommend avoiding this particular Shell location at 2890 Acton Road based on my recent experience with them.

On what will most definitely be my final visit, I selected the 87 grade gas (as I've done every time I've purchased gas over the last 25 years), and proceeded to fill my tank up.

Once my tank was full, I glanced up and noticed a total amount that caught me off guard. I was later reviewing my receipt, and noticed that the pump had somehow charged me for the premium gas that was positioned on the opposite side of the pump (and was exactly $1 more per gallon).

I immediately drove back to this gas station to share my experience with the attendant. In the end, he told me there was nothing he could do about it.

The total cost difference between the grade of gas I chose and what I was charged for came out to around $14.50 for a single fill-up. Needless to say, that isn't sitting well with me, and I'd like to issue a warning to others with hope that it prevents someone else from having a similar terrible experience with this business.

name: Jody Gray
text:
I am giving this store five stars for effort, when in reality, I have been so very frustrated with this pharmacy.  I have been a loyal Walgreens customer for at least 20 years, and have used Walgreens on the east coast, the west coast, and in between.  I’ve never had any issues with any other Walgreens as I have at this store.

To begin with, I’ve experienced phone wait times for up to an hour.  I just gave up on calling…I go directly to the pharmacy and wait to speak to the pharmacist.  I take a lot of meds, and there are times I have to personally request the pharmacy to fill certain prescriptions, as Walgreens online won’t allow me to electronically file certain scripts. Luckily I’m not far from the pharmacy, and driving over is no big deal for me. If you need to talk to someone in the pharmacy, just save yourself the frustration of calling.

I used to be a Job Coach, so I didn’t just want to hate this pharmacy…I wanted to understand what the problem was (is).  The problem is, they are always extremely busy, and maybe understaffed.  There have been times I have visited the store when there were at least 15 cars in line for the pharmacy; the line being wrapped around the building.  In addition there were also times where there were up to 10 people in line at the pharmacy.   I’ve sat and watched the employees working, and they are all working like crazy.  Nobody is on their phones, no one is standing around talking…they all seem to be working just as hard as they can.  In addition, I’ve always been treated with the level of kindness and professionalism that made me a loyal Walgreens customer many years ago. When I’ve been there I’ve heard the phone ringing constantly.  But In the pharmacy employees’ defense…they are so overwhelmed with customers in the store, no one has time to answer the phones.

Walgreens, if this pharmacy is understaffed, help them find some more employees!  There are a ton of people who depend upon this pharmacy for their medications.  Help this pharmacy to be better!

Sincerely, an extremely loyal Walgreens customer.

name: Beverly Nickerson

I was finally able to get there at a time there was only one person in front of me. They literally looked for this lady's prescription for almost 30 min and I had to leave. They could have at least had her wait to the side and grabbed the line full of people an mine and had the one person look for the meds. text: This specific pharmacy right here is amazing! It you want someone who actually cares about you as a person, go here! My mom came to visit from FL and accidentally left her medicine. Her heart is only working at 20% so her medicine is VERY important. I called the CVS in Jasper and the lady literally laughed at me and told me were were screwed when I asked what she recommend we do. Called here just to see and they were beyond fantastic. She understood the situation and had actually had it happen to herself before. She told me what to do and was beyond patient with my moms doctor and regular pharmacy. They really saved us, and we were able to get a weeks worth of her meds. I am beyond thankful for them because I get to spend the week with my mom instead of her having to drive back 7 hours the day after she got here.

The unsmiling and hostile woman behind the counter said  The sink! and did not bother to even point to it. I said thank you, looked around,found the sink, and reached for an empty paper cup. At this point the woman  shouted angrily You can't have that! And glared at me hatefully. I was shocked. I had never been treated like this, especially in the South. I do have a foreign accent. I do understand rules - she could have smiled and told me sorry, I cannot spare you a cup though you just spent 40 dollars on had here. Then I would have smiled too and bought some bottled water.      This woman is  a disgrace to your business. We will never stop by again. For your reference, this was around
4  pm  on Thursday April 6.

What a way to start a long weekend. I really do believe that nasty people better work in nonservice jobs. I am in a service job myself. Everything matters. Kindness and courtesy go along way. Alas, ugliness also does.

name: Phyllis Perez
text:
I ordered pet grooming clippers from what seemed to be a reputable company...four months later they hadn’t arrived and I opened a dispute with PayPal as this company ( Luol ) refused to refund me my money!! The tracking showed this package having originated in China...made its way to California and then mysteriously found its way to Australia of all places!!
PayPal was kind enough to refund my money and further to that closed the account that scammed me. They also warned me that companies like this just open up under different names only to repeat the same thing.
Unfortunately, within a few days, I saw the same item on Fb under  a different company name and within the same day another name and another name.
Come to find out this is called a “brushing scam” where they post fake reviews by fake people, only to charge people’s accounts for fictitious. I wrote my comments again and again to warn people not to purchase and finally reported them to Fb.
A few days ago I received clippers in the mail from someone named Jon at 2352 bent creek Rd, Auburn, Al 36830.
That led me to this article and the many reviews by people who experienced the same thing.
I am going to bypass the BBB this time and go to the FBI and maybe even ICE. This is obviously a sham and these people need to be stopped!!

name: Cam Brown

name: Jordan Arnold
text:
I went in with my mother to get a flu shot a couple days ago, and I wanted to get a video of me receiving a flu shot. (There are tons of videos circulating the internet of children, teens, and adults reacting to needles) and I was going to video myself receiving one with my mother's help because she too thought it would be funny.
We were both perfectly fine with putting our experience on camera, and did not feel as though it were violating our privacy.
The nurse, or woman with needle named Shay came in and just as my mother was about to get her shot, she tells me to turn off my camera. She would not provide services while being videoed. I was stunned and asked why and she proceeded to tell me it was a violation of HIPAA.
I was annoyed, but turned it off, not understanding what the deal was with videoing my esperience when countless others have done it IN DOCTORS OFFICES. When it came time for me to receive my shot she looked at me like I was crazy for jumping away from the needle and crying.
I DONT LIKE NEEDLES WHY DO YOU THINK I WAS RECORDING.
My arm was sore for days after the shot, which was probably my own doing for tensing up but she did nothing to even console her "patient". Not knowing much about HIPAA I went and asked some of my nursing friends and a phlebotomist I went to school with if there was a passage in HIPAA about a provider refusing service because of privacy on camera and both said no I even followed up on it by looking up HIPAA. Because the P in HIPAA stands for PATIENT not PROVIDER. Walgreens, if you don't want people videoing their experience (knowing what they are risking with their own privacy) please put up signs saying "no video or camera beyond this point" which will clear things up big time.
I will never get my flu shot at Walgreens again. Tell your "nurse" to work on their bedside manner.

text:
Nice that they are giving corona vaccine, but there were difficulties  encountered.
1st, cold call on my phone the morning of the appointment that my  Medicare insurance number is needed.... Well I was told never give out personal information over the phone.  When I arrived for my appointment time, I can provide at that time.

2nd  arrived for appointment 15 minutes early as instructed.   Went inside CVS, ( about 15 - 20 persons ) standing around at front door, and I noticed a second line ( 4-6 persons ) , and noticed there was another line down by the  Pharmacy another ( 4-6 persons ). The  woman in control at the door was quick to answer that there were problems with " Insurance " and that I should wait.  Standing for long periods of time for me is not possible.  After waiting for over 1 hour my name is still not called, and noticed that I have yet to see anyone that I first saw in the Pharmacy line has left.

Maybe those coming in for the vaccine appointment, should be politely informed of the extensive waiting time so that they can make a choice.  Personally I was not that comfortable around so many other masked people in a busy area.

name: Cheyenne Hamilton
text:
Posting for my grandpa who’s trying to get my grandma and great aunt covid vaccinated:

We drove 1 hour and 15 minutes to Bay Minette CVS for our vaccine appointments. My wife, Ramona and my 87 year old sister could not go inside to the pharmacy, due to physical constraints, to get their vaccines and they would not come outside to administer the shots. The pharmacist at Foley CVS has been administering our vaccinations for the past several years. She comes to our truck and it only takes a couple of minutes. She's a real blessing to us.  However CVS Foley doesn't currently offer covid vaccines.  We were so disappointed that the Bay Minette CVS personnel were so unaccommodating for their handicap patients. That's just another example of how people, the employees, of a particular location make a real difference.
*Wal-Mart Robertsdale (no available appointments for next 7days)
*Wal-Mart BayMinettee(no available appointments for next 7days)
*Baldwin CO Heath DP (vaccine will be available June 8th
No appointment times available at this time)
*CVS - None available at this time except Bay Minette
(no handicap) We will NOT be trying another CVS unless we can verify they will come out to the truck.
* Foley CVS Five Stars
* Bay Minette CVS Zero Stars

resp.text:
Hi Tony,

Retail gas prices are a reflection of the current function of supply and demand and are ultimately set by the individual retail sites, which are independently owned and operated. Many factors contribute to gas prices, which the Energy Information Administration discusses at the following page: http://www.eia.gov/energyexplained/index.cfm?page=gasoline_factors_affecting_prices

We are sorry to hear about your experience with the owners. We will pass this along to the Consumer Relations team, who will notify the owner of your experience.

Thanks,
BP

Then 3 hours later the Pepsi man was trying to get in to the store and his load fell over. I then helped him pick it all up and he got in the door.  Later on he came out and asked if I was out of gas or could he help.  He put in 10.00 for me.  Jason is his name and I appreciate that.   I had then already contacted my brother who was on the way also.   But the treatment I received from this employee really hurts the kind spirit of mankind.  Instead of asking what was gojng on and listening to what I was doing she immediately was on the defensive with you got to move. You are blocking my gas pumps costing me business.  It was 3 am.  I was the only one out there with my dog.  On the phone trying to get some money.   I only lived 20 miles away but I was on empty and I will always check before I leave the house and I will always have cash in the car.  I will never stop agajn at this station I will just run out of gas.

If you want and need a pharmacy and pharmacists that truly care about their customers, go to walgreens or any other place on the planet. Most places will work with you to RESOLVE any issues simply because it is not worth having bad reviews posted online for the world to see. WORD OF MOUTH can make or break a business.
There are alot of people who just love drama and will go straight to the internet to completely bash a business without even giving management the chance to rectify a wrong. Half the time they never even knew there was an issue until they were affected by a bad review.
Any issue I have ever had with this store was always resolved once I spoke with management and for that I give this Fred's in Evergreen a 5-star review.

I have always had a positive opinion of CVS, and have used the services for many years. Recently I switched to Walgreens for its convenient location on my usual routes. I have gone back to CVS for 2 reasons: 1) they’re a registered provider on my new insurance, and 2) they never bombard me with texts and reminders like Walgreens did, and the phone system is MUCH faster and easy to use, and I don’t have to talk to a recording at length with each order or call! The staff in the Pharmacy are always courteous and helpful. It makes my life MUCH less stressful.
Thank you CVS!

name: Elisa Blackburn
text: I had a prescription sent over from the urgent Care across the street, and had the worst experience with this pharmacy. The tech (didn't get her name, but she was a light-skinned girl with a wrap on her head) VERY obviously did not want to be there. She rolled her eyes several times while telling us she hadn't received the prescription yet. No big deal. We went to McDonald's and ate in the car, then came back through the drive thru about 20-30 minutes later. She was very aggravated to see us again. She got another girl (white girl with long, curly hair) to come tell us that they had just received it (which is bull-the doctor sent it immediately) and they were about to close, so they couldn't fill it. I absolutely believe they just wanted to go home, so they made up a story in hopes that we would just go away and come back in the morning, but we actually live 30 minutes away. We wanted to grab the prescription while we were still in the area; otherwise, we would have chosen a pharmacy closer to us. I wish we would have. Now my sick son has to wait another 30 minutes to an hour before he can go to sleep in his bed while we go back to the urgent Care, get the prescription transferred, then drive to another pharmacy. I hope your pharmacy girls have fun doing whatever was more important than getting my son his medicine.

name: Andrea Lovvorn
text:
Worst customer service I’ve ever seen from a pharmacy. CVS across the board has gotten lazy and is lacking in so many ways. I personally watched them answer the phone and continuously put patients on hold only to stand and talk to one another while counting. Two technicians and a pharmacist ran their mouths while the phone echoed “1 pharmacy call” over and over while they laughed and talked about their day, only to answer and ask the customer to hold until the phone started echoing “one pharmacy call” again and again. While a third was inputting RX into the computer at drop off. I watched them tell a customer in the drive through to hold while they pulled her RX only to stand and talk more.
Coming from surgery I was told that the wait for my RX it would be 2 hours minimum. We all know there is NO 2 hour wait for a “waiter” as Cvs calls them. I’ve never called this particular location and not been placed on hold less than 10 minutes. I now know why. CVS does not seem to care about the quality service they give like they once did. They do not appear to be understaffed, they appear to have a lazy work ethic and VERY poor bedside manner. In my opinion they need to clean house bc I wasn’t aware that the Caremark brand was willing to be represented in this manner.

That is not good customer service. She never thanked me for coming in when I went in to pay Nor at any time did she even produce a smile. Arrogant and condescending. I asked her name – she said J. I have always given this station five stars if I have to keep dealing with her I will move my business and tell others in the area how bad the cashiers have gotten recently.

text:
Update: regional manager personally called me and validated my concerns. Says a fix is coming, admitted to network issues and apologized for staff and network issues. Taking a wait and see approach. And adding back some stars.

About one out of every three times I come in to use my MapcoExpress discount the gas pump times out, causing me to change pumps and lose my reward discount. Tonight I stood there for over 10 minutes waiting, which is what the screen said to do. I pressed the call attendant button many, many times, to no avail. I finally went inside, and there was no one in there. Looked around and finally was given the international sign for wait a minute from one of the three employees in the back. I waited and was again told it wasn't their fault and there is nothing they can do, which I already knew. You have a telecom issue and never fix it. I don't care if it is a corporate office issue, it affects me, my time, my mood, and my price of gas. I drive by 15 stations to come to your station and yet it's not your problem. I'm aware it is my problem, businesses with customer focused attitudes make my problem their problem. Maybe you could start there...

name: Pete Odom
text:
After answering all questions asked by pharmacy cashier, I was told that I would be advised when single prescription was ready. It was apparent that the pharmacy was busy so I waited patiently in the pharmacy seating area. After approximately 40 minutes,  noticing that the seating area had emptied out at least 2 times, I once again went to cashier. Original cashier wasn't there any longer so I spoke to another who looked up my request.
I was told that nothing had been entered and had to once again answer basic questions.  Once that was done my prescription was filled Immediately.
I believe the pharmacist there are very professional but there seems to be an issue with attitude at the cashier level. Since there were several cashiers at the windows,  I don't believe it was an issue of inadequate staffing.

name: Chris Adams
text:
Typical overpriced specialty retailer.  The pharmacy is ok although it is so rare that I use them I can't speak much to that.  Usually, it's that I need something on the fly and they happen to be close by.  Everything is priced for people that use their card.  I can't stand all this card nonsense almost everywhere you go.  Price is $2.99 then get to the register and it's $5.99 without the card or whatever.  Random but don't bother buying ice cream here as they can't even handle it correctly so it melts by the time the get it put up so when you buy it it's iced up and no longer creamy as it should be.  Yes, that's an odd thing to mention but hey at least now you know.

Walgreens, stop with the card nonsense...seriously it's just ridiculous.

I'll go here if I have to for a prescription once every year or so but other than that it's just not worth coming here.

name: Meota Meow
text:
My insurance forces me to use Walgreens and I hate every time I go get anything for my dad since he is diabetic which means I frequently shop here to my dismay. No one should have to put up with nasty pharmacists or just staff who dont care? Called just today because we could only afford half of the insulin at the beginning of the month I call and I'm told that I didnt pick it up in a timely matter and that now the order is put back. Honestly I called for medicine not to be lectured rudely about something I cant control social security picks the day it arrives every month not me but before I could even explain she tells me I have to go get another copay dr visit to get more insulin then after talking a little more she says he has refills so which is it do I need to get my dr or does he have refills how much is it going to cost am I going to have to pay for a full prescription and she really just talked in a circle so I got off the phone

If you dont have to use them JUST DON'T there is  cvs across the street  just go there it cant be any worse then this wallgreens simply not possible

name: A L
text: I have had a total knee replacement. I wanted to fill my Percoset prescription. Pulled in drive thru, my friend driving put the prescription in box, the tech was just standing there watching, let the prescription fly out of the box on the ground. I couldn't get out and my friend has a bad hip so that was difficult. They said it would be about 25 minutes as usual.  We pulled off. Did another errand which took longer went back to Walgreens.....the same tech looks at us and says we can't fill the prescription because our system is down. Well why in the hell couldn't they call me and say they couldn't fill it? I was hurting and needed my meds. Does anybody have common sense any more? Had to get prescription and go to CVS wait another 20 minutes.  I never had trouble with RITE AID IN FULTONDALE. THEIR STAFF WAS VERY SMART. I AM GOING TO SEE IF MY INSURANCE IS ACCEPTED AT THAT LOCATION  WHICH IS NOW WALGREENS. SAME NAME BUT THE STAFF MAKES THE DIFFERENCE. THEY HAVE COMMON SENSE.

The whole staff in the pharmacy treated me horrible.  Beginning with totally ignoring me when I stood at the counter for several minutes with 5-6 people working in there and no one but me at the counter!  When some one finally did wait on me, my med was not ready; before all the ugliness was over they had kept me in there for over an hour while they waited on around 10-12 other customers not counting the drive thru!  Much more was said and went on towards me that was not professional nor was I treated fairly, however, I have already written a book and can not say it all here so I will write headquarters.  I did nothing nor said anything to them at first to deserve this treatment; but the more they pushed my buttons the more I got upset.  I still held myself back to what a lot of folks would have done.  This happened on the day crew July 5, 2017.  Thanks for letting me rant!

name: Denice Chavis
text: Was there at CVS in Dothan Al. on park and main. It was a little after 8am today and I was picking up my husband's medicine that required (2) IM needles to administer.  I always have to ask for these everytime. These people know it's a vial of medicine that I have been getting for months and months now and yet they never say do you need needles with that? So like all the times before I ask for needles and was told by a nice fuzzy male red headed pharmacy tech we have no needles. I said yet you sold me medicine that requires needles and yet you have no needles to sell me. The pharmacist lady obviously overheard our conversation and chimed in that CVS and Walgreens have been contracted to give the Covid vaccine to all nursing home people so all of their needles will be going to that. She then informed me that I could go to and I quote "Mom and Pop" drug store and they would be able to help me with the 2 needles that I need. I said my prescription card is CVS caremark and you send me mail telling me if I shop anywhere else but you, that the prices will be higher because I'm not using you and yet you sell me medicine I can not use because you have no needles. She said covid vaccine is our top priority right now. I said wow I thought the customer would be your top priority. She said you obviously dont understand the importance of this. I informed her I do. I'm a healthcare worker but what I dont understand is I've been asking for these needles long before a vaccine came out. How do you sell me medicine but no means to administer it. Is that what you tell people with their insulin. I'm changing our pharmacy to another pharmacy (NON CVS and NON Walgreens). Preferably one that is more willing to help me and my healthcare needs.

resp.text: Good afternoon Mr. Jamie sir my name is Ron the proud owner of the Knicker Knacker Market original form Freeport Grand Bahama over 19 years ago I came to the USA with two pieces of luggage to my name 13 years later I moved to Montgomery AL there was no grocery store downtown I worked at Capital City Club for 5 years during that time I worked several other jobs at a times my coworkers would tease me and ask me how many jobs do you have after 5 years we're up I decided to open up a grocery store out of my pocket with no help from a bank or any other lending institution I have been learning my business hands-on as I go not everyone was born with a silver spoon some of us have to work hard for an honest Living some of us had to start from the bottom to get to the top I have worked hard to get where I have gotten am sorry that you felt the need to be disrespectful you are one person but to my many other satisfied customers they would disagree with you but I thank you for your opinion, I pray for God to continue to bless you and I was behind the cash register, Shalom!

name: Shelby May
text:
Just left this store after Carol, the cashier, refused to help me. Went to check out through self checkout because there was nobody in the front. Was surprised to be carded for buying NyQuil. My neighbor has the delta variant and is having a hard time sleeping with the body aches. So, though I have no symptoms, I am masked. The register is dinging and saying that someone will come assist me pretty loudly. Carol walks right past me, tells an unmasked girl that she will help her at the register. I politely say, “excuse me, I just need you to verify my age. Could you help me really quick.” She stares straight at me and then completely ignores me. She begins carrying on a conversation with this girl, they are new best friends. The girl’s mom worked at CVS when she was in high school. So five minutes later, the manager comes to help me because the alarm was going off for so long!

Bottom line, CVS is a health service company and Carol is not representative of their mission or values. It’s pretty disappointing that someone with such little compassion and regard works at this type of establishment; the type of establishment people hope to count on when they are feeling their worst. You can not count on Carol.

name: Russell Meyers
text:
Typical Montgomery "professionalism".
Scheduled an MMR vaccine online yesterday. Got there few minutes ahead. They tell me they are doing vaccines in the drive-through. (?!)
What if a person has no vehicle? Not my case but true for some.
Go to drive-through. They ask for ID, fine. Then a bunch of other questions. They say they cannot find my appointment in the system. Then tell me to schedule another appointment online for this morning. Not happy but I did. (Note they did not ask if I had time this morning.)
I call to confirm an hour ahead. Getting through their phone system, the recording tells me no appointment is necessary for a vaccine. Hmm.
Pharmacist gets on the line, tells me that their MMR is out of stock. Something they could have told me yesterday.
Drama, poor work ethic, worked harder to NOT do something than they would if they had just done it.
Purely unprofessional.

name: Beth Haney
text:
Store 4858 Near Troy, Al
Stopped in to check on filling a prescription and use the restrooms. We were on a 5 hour road trip, had stopped for several restroom stops and this restroom was worse than any run down nasty gas station bathroom we had seen. The trash was overflowing, empty toilet paper rolls under the dispenser, no soap to wash your hands. The outside of the toilet had layers of dust and fluids streaming down. We asked an employee about getting some soap and informed them that the room needed some attention. She acted like that wasn’t her job. The men’s room was worse. It smelled of urine because the toilet and floor was stained with urine. While we waited for the girl to track down the soap we went to the pharmacy counter and had to ask for hand sanitizer because there wasnt any out on the counter. He said he was aware of the condition of the restroom and commented, “yeah, we’ve told them.”  I don’t know who “we or them” are but someone’s not doing their job. If the shift employees are not going to clean them they need to hire a janitorial service. For a place you go to care for your health, the sight of this place made me feel sick.

name: Patty Griffith
text:
After several managers had come and gone from the CVS on Chalkville Mountain Road and Grayson Valley Parkway there have been no improvements. I would frequently go in the store, which is right near my home and I would find a bell that said “ring for service”.  No one would come when I would ring the bell. I had to go hunting for someone to purchase my items.  There would be nobody at the front and nobody in sight; I would holler “hello, hello” and nobody would respond.  I finally found someone and asked who was the manager and was told the manager was Jimmy Jackson.  Every employee in there that has been fired and then rehired or hired in the first place has been rude, obnoxious and very unhelpful in every way. The shelves are always I stocked. When I go in to get my cat litter there is never any on the shelf; and I’ll ask if they’ll go back in the back, after they huff and puff, they will and come back and say “truck day is tomorrow.” When they say truck day is tomorrow it’s always on a different day.
As I went in there four days later, the shelves  were the same and they still did not have my cat litter. I politely asked the gentleman behind the counter if they had any in the back. The young lady behind the counter next to him said “she’s always like this” to another customer who was standing next to me. I have never been so humiliated and embarrassed the employees name was Cam. I will not be back.
If I could give this store a zero I gladly would.

name: Michele Smith
text:

text:
Over the past month or so the pharmacy at this location that use to be great A+ about getting your prescriptions out on time as promised and I would even get an alert on my phone when they were ready to pick up but lately it’s the total opposite.
What has happened?
Prescriptions are promised to be ready at a certain time and when you go to pick up those prescriptions at that promised time they still aren’t ready so you have to wait in line behind other customers with promised unfilled orders. What’s the point of telling a customer to wait 5 hours and it’ll be ready at 7:00 when you get there at 7:00 it’s not. If things don’t change soon I’ll be going somewhere else with my prescriptions. Customer service is always #1 and this CVS pharmacy isn’t providing that.

name: Amanda
text: Had a bad experience with a passport photo. They took forever taking the photo due to the camera dying and not having enough memory. The staff kept having to take my young child's photo because of the camera and took about 6 picture before it got right.  Took about 45 minutes. Submitted the photo with our application but it was denied due to the size of the head being too large. So we had to retake the photo at walgreens again and PRAY we get our passport in time for a very expensive trip. If we do not we will have to expedite new paperwork and this will all be due to walgreens not resizing the photo correctly. We asked for a refund which they would not give. The staff was as helpful as the could be on the first visit and I do not blame them for the equipment failure. But i believe due to their error we should have been offered a new photo and refund.

name: Voodoo Actual

When I finally got to the counter I was told they couldn't take any more prescriptions since they were so busy. I let the young lady know that I was just dropping it off for later when suddenly a sweaty behemoth of a pharmacist appeared. He informed me that he was to busy and he wouldn't fill it later either. I was further told that I should go somewhere else. No problem. This was my first and last experience with Walgreens - never spent a dime and never will. They should be required to pay me for my time though.

Am now on hold for the third time today an my doctors office is about to close and I'm starting to experience side effects from not being able to get my meds. This is not the first time this has happened. Shame on Walgreens for taking state ACA $ but not using it to provide decent care.

Got a coke. Even worse.
Returned it.
Went around the store and I cant find ANY cokes that arent expired and pepsis that are only good to like november and January in a few rare cases. Are their inventory people in a coma? Did they die? Get your meds here but dont shop here.

text:
I will never visit this location again. The employee that was working tonight/morning was one of the most rude people I've ever encountered. I greeted him with "Good morning, how are you sir?". He responded with only a cold stair as if I wasn't allowed or supposed to be there.

I had an arm full of stuff to purchase and he wasn't at a register when I approached so I unknowingly sat the items at the wrong one. When he eventually sauntered over instead of helping me move the items to the correct one, he just pointed and approached it and staired at me while I moved everything. I didn't mind having to move my stuff but, in my eyes, proper customer service would dictate the employee assist in moving everything because I had no idea I was at the incorrect register when I sat the things down. He also was not wearing a mask, even though there is a sign on the doors saying "masks required inside this facility".

Anyway, maybe I'm just being petty, but it just irked me the wrong way, him with his superior attitude and all. In the grand scheme of things im sure my contributions won't be missed, but treating people in the manner he did me will eventually lead to more people never returning. Management of this facility should probably look for some workers with at least a small amount of pride in their job. I get its only a fuel station attendant job but all jobs, especially ones dealing with the public, should show a little pride in their work and make the customer feel welcome.

I preceded  to the register to pay for my items while the person kept yelling at me.. I told the cashier let me pay for my items because I have to go to work. Several  customers left in shock during this person unprofessional act. If I can give this store a zero I would!! If you're looking for a place with great customer service skills this not your place. name: Jennifer Brown
text:
CONSIDER A DIFFERENT PHARMACY

So I'm currently on 3 calls with the same CVS to verify a prescription. The longest hold time is currently over 36 minutes. I'm going to leave it going until close to see if anyone ever answers.

Even walmart is better than this. Step your game up. I'll post a picture shortly.

UPDATE:
So after holding 1 hour 2 minutes (the middle call). Someone answered. Of course, the prescription wasn't ready "because a printer is down." This is standard practice for CVS in Center Point, which is why I was calling in advance. The guy on the line was so used to the lie it wasn't even sincere.

Asked when the prescription would be filled. He didn't know. Of course. Asked if I could have my prescription transferred to a different location. The guy said that I can, I just need to give my name and DOB.

1 hour hold times for calls if you need to speak to someone, and wait time for prescriptions are 20 to 45 minutes even if the prescription was sent 2 hours ago.

This isn't the first time, but it is my last using any CVS. Maybe they own Walgreens or have shares in Wal-mart or somewhere I can get better service.

name: Nitro Motors Wheel Repair
text: I would give ZERO stars if it was possible. Horrible customer service, rude and in my entire professional career in the automotive industry pumping fuel 5-6 times a day, I have never been treated like dirt or degraded in such a humiliating way.  I prepaid for my fuel among other things and in my haste drove away only to realize I did not pump fuel.  I immediately went back, however the pump was either reset or another customer took advantage of the free fuel.  I went back in to ask for assistance, hoping when meters were read and fuel was out of balance, or someone had reported the situation.  A shorter, middle-aged man with a thick accent would not allow me to ask a question, finish my sentence, much less explain the situation.  I was not looking for free fuel - simply there is nothing we can do. From the moment I spoke, he screamed, yelled, repeatedly exclaimed, "it's not my fault, it's not my fault!" and would not allow me to continue.  He belittled me and spoke down to me as though I was trash, with multiple customers waiting in line with their jaws dropped in disbelief.  I simple gave up, gave him $10.00 to prepay for fuel (again). But he continued his tyrant and I had to ask several times for my receipt before he finally handed it to me.  At that point, I wanted my receipt, my new purchase and to leave.  If this gentleman is the manager or owner, I certainly have lost respect for him and absolutely refuse to visit Exxon in Saginaw, AL. A little common courtesy goes a long way.  As I stated, I wanted nothing for free and someone else benefited from my loss, fine, they are better for it, but to be treated as I was, while spending money at his store is a true testament to the type of business he runs.  Horrific.

text: This place doesn't even deserve a one-star. One of the technicians here stole half of my prescriptions. Now, I'm from out of town and this was my first and last time using this Walgreens. I went on a Thursday evening, and dropped off my prescriptions, then I went out to dinner. Afterwards I came back to Walgreens, there was a brunette at the register who was rude. I thought, she must be tired because she didn't look too good. I paid for my medication and walked out of the pharmacy. I went back to my place and noticed half the prescription was missing! I thought that's strange half my medication is missing and I just left the pharmacy that's never happened before, so I assumed it was probably a mistake.  When I finally got in contact with the pharmacy, I explained what happened and a woman responded saying she needed to check their records. After a few seconds she comes back on the line to tell me their counts for the prescriptions were accurate and she couldn't do anything about it. I said, I will come up there with the prescription bottles to discuss this! Then she proceeds to tell me she's the Pharmacy's Manager. At this point, I was getting upset! I told her this pharmacy charged me FULL price for a months supply of prescriptions then only gave me half of it. I told her, I had to pay out of pocket for this and I want to be reimbursed.  She continued to say there's nothing she could do.  Well, that's just too bad, because for a "Manager" not to even attempt to investigate  problems when a customer is genuinely upset and telling the truth about a bad experience just baffles me. Why isn't this manager more concerned that a technician took someone elses medicine from the pharmacy's safe and then falsifed records to get away with it?! She's kept saying there's nothing she could do. Really?! Why don't you fire the employee, so this doesn't happen again. Stealing medicine is illegal, but it's ok I know EXACTLY what to do and I will be making a police report about that employee and this Pharmacy.

name: Fred Shiels
text: I gave one star because they didn’t have an option for Zero!!!  These people at the Carter Hill store are the most RUDE, unprofessional “employees” I have ever encountered anywhere. name: Charge Barge
text: My experience sucked.  They apparently lost my first prescription on a controlled substance.  The pharmacist thought I was lying at first, assuming I was out for drugs.  Then realized that I got a notification from them that my prescription was delayed for the prescription prior to stopping by to pick it up.  They then apologized without giving me my medications.  It was out of their hands, so, I figured, no big deal.  I sent in the second one without a problem.  Today, I returned and I found out they're waiting for a prior authorization for the second medication.  The first one in the morning called my doctor's office and told them to disregard the first prior auth, and then the second pharmacist (Brittni H.) in the afternoon was still waiting for the prior auth that the first one was supposed to send.  Now, prior authorizations take a while to process, so they sadly just wasted a whole day of lack of processing, much to the chagrin of both me and my physician's staff (since we were both given the runaround).  I should really sue the pants off the pharmacists involved in these shenanigans here.

Finish it off with a cup of sweet tea. ❤ (Obviously I like their fried fish fillets.)

Also, they have since remodeled the restrooms and have added showers for $10.00 each. Dont listen to the folks who are fussin' in the comment section here. Come on in and try out Cafe 30, great truck parking (if you get in at a decent time) and friendly folks inside. 👍🏻👍🏻

Living in a truck these bathrooms are my only options and I've never been so pissed, sad sad excuse for a truck stop! text: I’m not one to leave reviews often but I’m doing this to bring it to the attention of the staff here. I dropped off my prescription at 7:15 and she was so sweet and said they would be able to get to it before closing so I told her I would wait over on the side. She very sweetly made sure i was signed up to be notified via text. 30 minutes later I got a call they needed my Insurance Info. I went back to the window and they said they actually didnt and I asked her how long it would be and she said 15 to 20 minutes because they are 3 hours behind. I told her I would wait since I had already been waiting 30 minutes. She apologized and said OK and then 35 minutes later I was still waiting. I ended up leaving because I had my two-year-old with me who needed to get in the bed and will have to make a special trip back bar. I am now home and still haven’t been notified it’s ready which means it’s now been 40 minutes (on top of the 30 before they called me for insurance) since she told me 15-20. I feel that if someone is waiting in your parking lot, there would be some more urgency or a suggestion that i should plan to come back. There was no one else in the drive-thru and the parking lot was empty, so I am certain I was one of the only ones waiting on a prescription. This is just super poor customer service.

After being a CVS customer since the late 80s or early 90s, all my prescriptions, including my son's and parent's prescriptions, are now transferred to Walmart.  I will never visit CVS again. We will never grace the door of another Walgreens and we will tell everyone we know! Terrible experiences there! Also they discourage use of the GoodRX card for those that are uninsured!

name: Leigh
text: Went to have a prescription filled a couple of weeks ago. Was told it was going to be about an hour or an hour and a half. Since it was days before qualifying exams for my masters program, I decided to try and wait it out instead driving to my house back, then back to cvs, and then back to my house, because I had my computer and could study. About an hour goes by, and all I hear from the other side of the cash registers is gossipy talk, complaining and conversations of “when did you get here?” “Oh, so we both get off at seven,” etc. I ended up getting sick of hearing it and bought a couple gaterades and asked the girl who had just clocked in and who was checking me out how much longer it would be. A girl, who had not helped me the first time but had just overheard the initial conversation, chimed in before she could inquire with them and said “an hour to an hour and a half at least”. I went home, living less than two miles from the cvs and right after I kicked off my shoes and got set up at my desk I received a message my prescription was ready. Less than 15 minutes later. Unprofessional and unhelpful due to the pettiness and disregard of customer service from pharmacy staff. Highly recommend going to the CVS on Glenn Avenue instead of this one. I’ve never had a problem with them, and pharmacy staff member Lee is my favorite. Always so kind, even when backed up with “17  prescription orders” to fill before my own, unlike south college.

Sure enough, the manager came to the front and activated the register, and in a very snarky tone told me I "didn't need to be upset" when all I did was point out that their store had an ongoing technical issue.  I will be notifying corporate since clearly not even store management has an interest in being professional.  I was also not given a receipt; I've worked in retail and I know that the only conceivable reason a receipt wouldn't be given is so that the employee names wouldn't be disclosed, so whoever worked on the night of April 4, 2018 around 9:10 PM should be held accountable.

text:
Hands down, the absolute BEST Bar-B-q not only in town but in St. Clair county. They are proud of it but it's not reflected in their prices.
Teeth are not required for any of their quality, well prepared meats. Rib meat literally falls off the bone. So tender you can almost eat the bones themselves. You choose the sauce you prefer and their menu is large. They offer family meals as well as party size orders. There is decent barbq nearby in town but none of it even comes close to this store's fine Q.
Today i was served a HUGE T-bone steak with potato and side salad for $11.99.
Your simply not gonna beat that.
And if your in the mood for a simple bbq sammich then they have a sammich, bag-o-chips and 20 oz. drink deal. Trust me when I tell you. It's worth it. Stay away from "gas station sushi" but this bbq is worth a 50 mile drive and thats the honest truth.
Enjoy.

text:
If I could give it a 1/2 star I would. Absolutely unprofessional staff except for maybe 1 person and that’s the only reason for the half point. I’ve been forced to use this pharmacy for a little over a year and  every single time I have had to pick up my monthly prescription (same thing every single month) they tell me a time for pick up and it’s never ready. I usually have to call and wait on hold for 15-20 mins just for them to tell me they haven’t gotten started on it even though it was supposed to have been READY an hour before. Not only that but I no longer have insurance through my job and I pay out of pocket, but for some reason they still make me run around every month explaining to them how I pay out of pocket and have no insurance to verify so they will actually get my medicine together. And like I said I get the same thing every single month.  I pay the same way every single month. This is the worst pharmacy in the history of pharmacies. I’ve used a cvs in warrior AL before and they are amazing so it isn’t the company or brand CVS. They just picked the wrong person to run the Jasper CVS.  And last complaint. I have made numerous complaints about how the pharmacy is treating the patients and I always get the same thing. “We are so sorry we will have the pharmacy manager call you to discuss your issues”. Never heard from anyone and issues still aren’t fixed. Worst run pharmacy if you value your time and money and don’t enjoy having to run around and do the pharmacies job just to pick up your monthly prescription.

So excuse my rant, but,  I’ve had it with this place after a year and a half of trouble. It’s sad when your moving and one of your moving “perks” is getting to use a better pharmacy. Please! someone go to work there and fix this place for the sake of all the people that need their medicine to survive.... because if it’s up to this place... they won’t.

text: My experience at this CVS was simply horrible. Let me explain. There have been multiple occasions when the pharmacy staff told me I have 0 refills, and I hear verbatim from my doctor that I should have a prescription for one- year- supply. Please keep in mind the phone consultation I had with my doctor regarding the difficulty receiving my medication cost $$- so it bothers me that they refuse to refill my prescriptions when I have refills. It is a shame they do not train ALL pharmacy staff to have the competence to troubleshoot any insurance plan issue that arises. These staff members have an ethical responsibility as healthcare professionals to help- that they lack.

name: J Kindred
text:
I drive nearly 5 miles out of my way to shop at this particular CVS. There's one near my house, about 4 miles away. But the personal, hospitable, kind, compassionate & knowledgeable staff that I encounter at this store is more than worth the extra time. One's relationship with their pharmacist is a very close & personal experience. I've sadly found that many pharmacists seem to have little or no respect for those who are essentially their patients.
What earns this location the rare 5 star rating is that the golden qualities of the pharmacist & their pharmacy staff is found in every employee with whom I've had interaction. Honestly, Corporate should utilize this store as an example of the standard they need to see in every one of their pharmacies/ stores.

name: Jesse Pope
text: Not surprised to see they have below a 3 star rating already. Just moved to the area used CVS my whole life 8 different branches across 5 cities and this place by far was the worst pharmacy experience iv ever had. Employees are rude and reluctant to offer any kind of help. I have used the same medication for years I just needed a refill. None of my insurance or Dr. Information has changed but somehow they claim it has. After calling my Dr. (Phone consultation $20) reassured me the problem was on their end and he didn't want me to be without my meds so he sent in another refill. When I arrived they said I would have to pay full price wich I could barely afford it . Not wanting to argue with someone who could clearly care less I agreed and they said it would take about 15 min. I arrive one hour later to find they forgot to fill arguably my most important perscription of them all. To make matters worse I'm flying out of town the next day with alot less money and without my medication.  Awful group I recommend going litarally anywhere else but here.

I just wanted to make sure she heard me! Called Pharmacy manager and she said "well she thought you were yelling at her." So that is a excuse to end the call. What about her short patience/lack of customer service. I had been on hold for hours, what if I had an urgent need? I moved to Alabama to experience this kind of behavior? One star for the pharmacy is a compliment. I can't wait to fill out the survey for this chain! I do not feel safe getting my medicine from this location. I honestly felt like we all developed a relationship over the years. They are very nice people. Once again, you are paying for connivence. They have Indian food that you can try. text: Mostly decent folks working there but on this particular occasion, when ringing up my 1 item I noticed that the price was a dollar higher than the advertised price on the shelf. I informed the clerk, once he finished his chicken nuggets, of the error. He begrudgingly went to look, verified that I was not telling a falsehood and responded with, "well, that's just what it's ringing up as." Unsatisfactory!! This is the same situation I encountered at the Memorial store a few weeks back but the clerk, after 5 minutes of hashing it back and forth and basically calling me a liar, finally corrected the price. This is not a new sticker to go up today as it was the SAME item a few weeks ago! I do a lot of my business for these items at Mapco but if this is the kind of treatment I can continue to expect, I will gladly carry that business elsewhere and enthusiastically pay for my items from now on.

resp.text: Alex, We apologize for the experience you described and we can assure you that behavior goes against our culture standards. We have alerted the District Manager over that location to take swift action.

name: Emily Busby
text: The two pharmacist are usually very helpful and nice and the cashiers are too but they give me trouble just about every month concerning my prescription. I take one prescription a month which is a schedule three or four narcotic I believe. I go to my doctor and he writes my new prescription every 28 days. I take two a day which equals 56. I drive almost two hours to this doctor and live in a rural area that never has this medicine so I always stop at this Walgreens and every time they tell me they can’t fill it until the next day or I have to wait two days even tho my doctor schedules my next appointment on the exact day my medicine runs out. For example I got my prescription filled there last month on 2/5/20. Went yesterday after my appointment to fill my script for this month which ran out yesterday. Waited in traffic and in line for over 20 minutes only for the cashier to tell me she can’t fill it until tommorow. I didn’t even waste my time explaining to her that I couldn’t turn around and drive two more hours again the next day or that my medicine ran out yesterday so technically I could have gotten it filled two days early as per the narcotic laws. I’m not sure if she dosent pay attention to the quantity and counts thirty days or she just dosent care to actually read the directions on the prescription. This is also a medicine that if I don’t take it causes extreme withdrawals so I ended up having to drive 30 plus miles out of my way and wait two to three days for another pharmacy to fill it. Got home and called and asked them via the phone if I was eligible to get it filled yesterday and the lady said yes. Needless to say these people don’t understand that some of these medicines are people’s lifeline and they don’t understand the danger and inconvenience of having to drive all around the country and risk your health all because they can’t take twenty seconds to read a prescription look up last day it was filled and count 28 days. Drove 30 miles to another pharmacy keep in mind another WALGREENS pharmacy and they told me I could have gotten it filled Sunday. Done with Taylor road. They also charge me(no insurance same medicine and same amount every month never changes) anywhere from 180$-300$ went to another Walgreens paid 112$ explain that.

name: Jessica Heyer
text:
BEWARE!!  CARD SKIMMER ON CREDIT CARD MACHINE AT THE REGISTER INSIDE THE STORE.
When I used my debit card at this store on July 17, 2018, I was required to enter my pin # two times- once at the beginning of the transaction and again at the end of the transaction. I Asked the cashier why I was required to enter my pin twice and she quickly looked away nervously and didn't respond. I then turned the machine and looked closely at the side where cards are swiped. The machine appeared to have an overlay that had been mounted to the credit card machine. When I looked up, the cashier looked away quickly and would not make eye contact.

The following day, July 18, I began to see fraudulent charges posting to my bank account. I reported the charges to regions and was told by the bank manager that it appeared that someone had cloned my debit card. Regions is opening an investigation into the fraud.

TO THE OWNER OF THIS STORE-
YOUR EMPLOYEE (white female with brown hair, approx late 30s to 40s) that was working the register on July 17, 2018 around 1pm is a thief!!
If she stole from me, she'll steal from you and the rest of your customers!!

resp.text:
Thank you Erin for your review.  I am looking into this situation and please know that I take this issue  very serious.  I would love to speak to you to acquire more details . Country Convenience has never had this happen before.
Thank You   Patti Middleton  251-964-5674  or 251-747-7581

text: This Walgreens is always extremely busy. I’ve had to wait for 20 minutes in the drive through. They take at least 45 minutes to fill prescriptions. Then someone told me it would be a while because 3 people were in front of me and the vials had to be taken out of the refrigerator to get to room temperature. They don’t seem to have enough staff. Either it’s that or they do not have a good workflow process. Do anything you can to avoid this location. They are very scattered and seem very unorganized. At least the girl was polite and told me it would be a while. That’s why they got 3 stars instead of 1. Time is valuable though and no one should have to wait for more than 10 minutes to get a shot. The actual shot doesn’t take that long. Because of this I left and don’t know when I will reschedule or if I will reschedule. But it won’t be at this location.

text: I made the mistake of having a prescription sent to alabaster location at 5:40 when they were closing at 6. I stood in line and had prepared to ask them to send my prescription to another pharmacy if it was too late. They agreed and said the other pharmacy would have to call them, which they said they would. I asked if I was set to leave, was given the okay, so I headed to other pharmacy. They call me and say walgreens never answered their phone, that it went straight to operator saying they were closed. So, I head into traffic to go to hoover's 24 hour walgreen's pharmacy and I call ahead so they know to get it ready since it is a 30 minute drive. I was on hold for 25 minutes before they picked up. I figured--they must be super busy. 5 minutes later, I pulled in and there was no line, no rush, no hurry... they told me I had to wait another 15 minutes. When I inquired about why I had to sit on hold for 25 minutes if they weren't busy, "I dont know" was all I got. This woman could see I'd been crying (from worry over my kid) and I didn't get an apology, a rush job, kindness, nothing. If they had picked up their phone, they could have done the transfer for me at 6, and I could have had the meds to my sick child an hour earlier.

name: Sarah Trotti
text: The pharmacy has been so unhelpful. I am a student at The University of Montevallo and I am not from the area thus promoting me to transfer my prescriptions down here. This process has tried to take place every day for the past three days and I am finally giving up. The first day it took me 10 minutes before I could talk to anyone and when they finally answered they said their phones are down. That in itself was sketchy because I was talking to them through their phone system, but I figured that they got something working. I gave them my information and they said that they would get that in and text me from their personal phones (that in itself is odd) when it was ready. I never got that text. The next day, around the same time, I went down to the store to pick up school supplies and I asked them about my prescriptions. They had to take my information again as their phones were down and their computers were acting up the day before and they didn't get to my order. They asked me when I needed it and I said the next day and they told me they would call it in right then. The final day, at the same time of day, I called them and checked my status of my prescriptions by putting in my information that they had to take twice (well technically three times as they asked me twice the first day for my information). They said that they couldn't find my order. They have some issues they need to work out if they want to be in this business as my prescription is actually important to my health.

text: I had just gotten in the store good when they played the announcement that they were closing in 5 minutes and I needed to bring my purchases to the front of the store to be checked out. I didn't have any purchases yet and according to my cell phone, I still had 15 minutes before the official closing time. I thought I'd at least be able to pick up the important things on my list and that shouldn't take any longer than 5 minutes. As I started walking toward the back of the store, the cashier yelled for me to come check out right away. I informed her of the time and asked what the urgency was all about, and she told me that their system was problematic and that it would automatically close out the day 10 minutes early, on occasion. If this were to happen, the transactions for the day would be inaccurate, and I understood what a mess that would be for the accounting people, so I told her goodnight and left without buying anything. It was only a 10 minute drive to Hoover, and the Walgreens there is open 24/7 and never closes. They really need to get the system fixed asap so that more business isn't turned away from that store.

name: John O'Dell
text:
We stopped mainly to use the restroom but upon entering, we were so amazed by the merchandise, the cleanliness of the store and the sparkling restrooms, we had to grab something to eat at the adjacent restaurant.
The burger and onion rings that we ordered were beyond heaven, beautifully cooked and prepared.
The burger was made of one pound of beef and cooked to perfection with just the right amount of condiments and pickles.
My wife and I shared a single burger cut in half and almost couldn’t finish it.
The onion rings were sweet and fried in the perfect batter and were filled with flavor like they should be.
Do not pass up an opportunity to stop by and meet the friendliest people in Alabama as well as the cleanest restrooms for three states.
But most of all....DO NOT pass up the chance to eat some of the best food in the south.

text: I started using this gas station within the last 2 years. In the past I never really cared for the location tho now I'm not sure why. I rarely go elsewhere.  Their icee's are fire,  they carry Tastycake powdered donuts, nice selection of wine- I'm kinda assuming this.  I know nothing about wine but they have a bunch of different ones so I figured the possibility was high. The employees are super nice. One lady (who loves Alabama football) did me an absolute solid. "I" accidently left my 4yo's cup in the store while she was working. I had no idea.  Searched everywhere (I thought) for 2 days.  We have other cups, too many actually but he prefers the one abandoned. Can't blame him,  I have my own cup that no others can live up to. I get it. We went back to the store on day 2. While checking out she says "oh yeah" or something of the sort. She walks away, comes back with cup while telling me I'd left it. Glad she cleared that up cause home invasion had popped in my mind. It is a Cars cup after all. I apologize to Trussville PD explaining false alarm and hang up. That's a joke, they have me blocked. Anyway, I thank her a bunch, tell her how happy I am to have it, 4yo says "thank you" cause he should. I'll allow note taking just this once. We leave, I hear something fall off car. I stop and back up only to hear a crunch. It's pretty loud. Reluctantly I step out of the vehicle and start laughing hoping to lighten the blow. I ran over my chips. Didn't see that coming did you. Deuces.

name: James and Tara Hutchison
text: Terrible customer service in the pharmacy department by Kevin. We went to this Walgreens in between training assignments for the Navy. I am currently 8 and a half months pregnant. I had two prescriptions that needed to be filled. One of which was fine, but the other needed my docs authorization for the refill. That is standard for that particular medication, and at all other Walgreens has never been an issue. Kevin proceeded to inform me in an untactful manner that the medication was expired and had no other refills allowed. Both statements were untrue. The medication did not expire until 2020, and while the prescription required my docs authorization that can be obtained very simply by contacting my docs office like every other Walgreens has done in the past. If someone does not want to do their job then get out of that field. I will never go back there or encourage anyone I know to go back.

text: Hubby went to pick up my daughter’s prescription today and they have no medicine and we are not even in their computer system...🙄 Been going there for 5ish years off and on. My husband definitely gets super mad 😡. He calls me in an attempt to clear things up and while I am on speaker phone the pharmacist walks off and says “Im not arguing with a phone😯”. Now I have to go to Walgreens to show Terry P. the notification on my phone that says my prescription exists!! Get to the store. Calmly startover. I say you know you could have saved me a trip if you had taken the phone from my husband and agreed to talk to me over the phone. To this he scoffs and rolls his eyes 👀!! Transfer prescription to Grant Pharmacy eventhough I have to drive to get it! In the 20 years when i use Grant Pharmacy I get exceptional service. One day they forgot to put my prescription in my bag and drove it to Huntsville for me!! I never meant for this prescription to go to Walgreens but my doctor sent it there and I gave them the benefit of the doubt because we use them for little stuff and things that we need right away. I will never use them again and Terry P. will sleep just fine tonight because apparently he doesn’t have to say Im sorry for your inconvenience. Im sorry we couldn’t find your daughter in the computer and you had to make two trips!! Nope just a scoff and an eye roll! Obviously his pay is not tied to customer satisfaction. Im just one less customer for him to worry about!! Oh well I will miss the convienence of running in the store for multiple other things!!

text: This used to be a pretty decent fuel station with a pretty good deli. The deli, the actual store, the restrooms, everything. At 6:30 A.M., the coffee bar was out of everything but decaf, the creamer machines are out of service, and the whole thing looked like kindergartners had played in it! If this is in fact a Circle K, it is one of the sorriest ones I have ever been in. If you can just hold it for one more exit, I would highly recommend passing this place on by.

text: Prepaid for $20 on diesel in an F250 while helping our daughter move and they held $300 for about a week. The bank shut off our card because of suspected fraudulent activity immediately. Called to find out what happened, everyone was very rude and less than helpful. We had to wait for new cards to be mailed out. We haven't been back since, there are plenty of much better choices in the area, and we have told all of our friends to be very cautious. Terrible, terrible  choice to do business here. It was much better prior to changing from BP. I just feel sorry for people traveling that don't know better.

resp.text: Hi Thomas, we are sorry about your recent experience. We have passed on your message to our local management team. Please feel free to contact us via email https:// www.circlek.com/contact-form for further assistance.
