text: Everyone is friendly and respectful

name: Terry L. Catlett
text: Leslie, Dede, and Rose are awesome and always makes you feel welcome and at home.

resp.text: Thank you

name: Amanda Whitman
text: They are closed at 10 pm on Saturday night when it says 24 hours on that day.......

name: The Queen of Death
text: Always nice friendly faces no matter what time it is.

name: Matthew Lincoln
text: Very friendly employees and very kind althought sometimes it takes a while for the main guy to understand English havent been disappointed yet and it's the only gas station actually open 24/7 so that's a plus

name: Lynn Pope
text: One of the best burgers ever! The store/ Cafe was very clean and well organized, our food was cooked to order, the fries were fresh  and the staff was very friendly. Lisa was very kind and helpful. We will make the drive again. Thank you for a great experience 💜

resp.text: Thank you Lynn for your review! We hope to see you again soon!

name: Sierra Nave
text: My husband ordered the Blue Hole burger & tater wedges. He said it tasted like a homemade burger. Don't get no better than that. It was only a 1/2 pound of meat, but this burger was huge!

resp.text: Thank you for your review! We do strive for the homemade taste!  Look forward to seeing you again!

name: PR Heinl
text: Good food, a little slow on service, but they were busy. So, I'll give them a pass, the staff was friendly, enjoyed the visit. In response to the reply: I understand, still a great experience. Enjoyed the bacon cheeseburger, it was excellent.

resp.text: So glad you enjoyed your food. Sorry to hear about the service we are short staffed at the moment but doing our best to bring in new help. Hope to see you again soon.

name: Shana Durdin
text: Stopped here for lunch after hiking at Little River NP. We had burgers, bologna sandwiches and BLT’s and everything was so good! Lots of picnic tables outside to hang out and eat!

resp.text: Shana we are so glad you guys choose  to stop and have lunch with us. We do appreciate your feedback we depend on our customers letting us know when we get it right. Please stop by the next time you get a chance. Thanks so very much.

name: Eden Smith
text: My husband and I stopped in for a quick dinner and discovered karaoke night! We were quickly served and it was the best cheeseburger and fries in town. Food was hot fresh and prepared just the way one would want. Bathroom was also squeaky clean and all attendants were courteous and made us feel welcomed! We will definitely return! I just feel like this place needs more recognition!

resp.text: We are so glad you guys had a good experience with us and look forward to serving you again soon.

name: Brenda Bone
text: Awesome food, very friendly staff and I will go back. I had the steak and cheese sandwich with okra.

resp.text: Brenda you are so kind to take time to write us such a great review. Thank you and hope to serve you again soon.

name: Jeffrey Hudson
text: Food was amazing,  Cheese sticks, patti melt for me, and my wife loved her chicken sandwich. Great value and prices are good. Homemade ranch was the perfect finish.

resp.text: Thank you for your review! We appreciate your business and hope to see you again soon!

name: Shannon Marsicano
text: We stopped here after a hike at the waterfall. Staff was all friendly and pleasant to meet! Also BBQ pork sandwiches with slaw from the cafe were on point!

resp.text: Thank you Shannon for your feedback great way for us to know our customers and how we are doing. We hope you will come back soon. Have a great weekend.

name: Richard Hartline
text: Great food and nice people. My wife and I love everything we have ordered. They serve breakfast, lunch, and supper. You can eat from the hot bar or order off the menu. Good portions, too. So far, I've ordered take out, but they have seating for about 30 people. It is also a convenience store and gas station.

name: Luann Chastain
text: Yummy!  Everything is cooked after you order!  Really good bacon burger.  Patty filled the bun and was really flavorful and juicy!  Worth the twisty road to get there.

resp.text: Thank you for your review! We look forward to seeing you again! Have great day!

name: Clark L
text:
We were visiting the Little River Canyon area and stopped by. We were warmly greeted as we came in and also chatted with the folks behind "the grill". I asked what the favorites were on the menu and the prompt reply was "really, everything is good." Well, I can't vouch for everything, because we only tried the breakfast burritos 😊 The good: ample portion and tasty.
The so-so : rather salty and it took QUITE a while to prepare. Now, since we were meandering and not in a hurry, not a problem for us , but, you may want to be aware. Also have some Tshirts, souvenirs and grocery items ( that you pass on the way to a clean bathroom).

name: Todd Milsaps
text:
Granted there's not a lot of competition in the immediate area... But, having said that, the food and prices here are worth bouncing in for a hot meal if you are visiting Little River Canyon National Park. No need to make the drive into town to eat at a chain restaurant.
The staff is always very nice and you'll get your burger / chicken / BBQ quickly and be back at the Hippie Hole satisfied and full.

resp.text: Thank you for your kind review! We appreciate your business and are glad you stopped in to see us!

name: Dustin Morgan
text: Incredible service!! Friendly staff!! Delicious food!! We stopped in after driving past for lunch and had a great experience!! Here on vacation and would definitely recommend to anyone passing by!!

resp.text: Thank you so much we try hard and truly appreciate all of you guys.

name: Alex Harry
text: This place is great. Amazing food, friendly staff. Wonderful after a day out climbing I  the little river caynon. Would highly recommend 👍

resp.text: Thank you so much Alex for taking the time to leave us a review.  We appreciate your kind word and you business we hope to serve you again soon.

name: SlushyCatDude
text: This place is a very great store. the place has become more and more popular with a new owner. not a fast food place it's a great food place. lately, they have been jam-packed, but they still deliver. all staff are hard working and don't slack off. some people don't understand that their not a fast food place they're a restaurant. they can't make great food fast when understaffed. but if you wait a while talking to the locals or look around the store while they make the food you'll be surprised how great the food is. many people can't wait and that's understandable but don't say that they are a bad store if you don't have the patience to get great food.

resp.text: Thank you for your review and your understanding of our desire to always put out the best food possible.  We appreciate your kind words.

name: Marilyn Custer
text: Coming from Geraldine we were looking for a Mom n’Pop place for breakfast and this is what we found. Don’t be deceived by the store front. The food was good, really good, and the people were so friendly. We were glad to find it and will be back!!

name: Sue In TN
text: I read about this place online, and since we were headed up to the Little River Canyon Preserve, we decided to stop in here for a quick lunch.  Based on the reviews, it sounded wonderful.  I got a cheeseburger combo which was only a little over $6.00 and included my drink.   Wow.... I really think it was the best cheeseburger that I've ever had.... the french fries were those 'crinkle' kind and were so good... not one bit greasy.  Our food was ready very quickly, and everyone there was so nice and friendly.  Don't pay any attention to that poster who only gave it a one star.  It seems as though they were there during the World's Longest Yard Sale which brought so many people to the area, and they must have been swamped.  That is only once per year...... it's not a typical occurrence for them to be slow.  Focus on all the other reviews which are 5 stars.

resp.text: Thank your for your nice review. We appreciate your business!

name: Laura McKenzie
text: The grilled chicken sandwiches were delicious.  Our order was accidentally picked up by another family. The staff quickly cooked, from scratch, a new order and were as kind as could be.  Great place to stop after hiking.

resp.text: We appreciate your kind words and your understanding that accidents happen.  Please come eat with us again soon.

name: Tabitha Kinser
text: Over priced and slow getting out. Food was cold.

name: Carmel McNeese
text: Just ate here, and my husband and I were pleasantly pleased. Friendly staff, big portions, and delicious food! No long wait,  to boot!

resp.text: Thank you for taking the time to let us know how we are doing. We have a great staff who can put out delicious food and we all take great pride in our work. We hope to see you guys again soon.

name: Jason Baldwin
text: Friendly staff unable to put out food.  I arrived at 2 p.m. on Saturday with a big appetite and high hopes after reading G reviews.  I ordered a cheeseburger at the inside window and sat down with my self-serve drink.  It should have been a tip-off that NONE of the other 10-12 seated customers had any food, only drinks.  The eating area was full of flies, and the floors were pretty dirty.  I waited and waited and waited.  After 25 MINUTES OF WAITING, some of the people there before me still did not have any food. so I cancelled my order, paid for my drink, and left.  I know this place has lots of fans, but on this particular Saturday, they seemed incapable of putting out burgers.

resp.text: We appreciate your input and it was unfortunate for you and us that you stopped in at such a busy time of the day.  We do apologize and would like you to know we are not a fast food restaurant.  We make all food to order, meaning no staging of precooked food,  our cooks prep all ingredients fresh daily.  We like to say we are not fast food we do good food fast.  With increased visitation to Little River Canyon we have become well know especially for our burgers.  If you are ever in the area again please give us another visit I promise you we are worth the wait.

name: Suzanne Phillips
text: We had the lunch special and loved it! Highly recommend this place just outside of the Little River Canyon National Preserve. Great friendly service, good prices, and indoor/outdoor dining. Hit the spot!

name: Sharon Williams
text: Love the updates. Staff are so friendly and food is delicious!

resp.text: Thank you Sharon! We are all so excited and proud of all the improvements both inside and out. We have an excellent staff who truly want each customer to have the same experience you did. We appreciate the feed back thanks for your time. We look forward to serving you again soon.

name: Keller Rongey
text: Great food. VERY pleasant staff. Clean and friendly.

name: Michael Culberson
text: We stopped to have lunch after driving around the canyon today. The hamburger was DELICIOUS!!!!! If you’re anywhere near the area, please stop here. The prices were low and the food was great.

resp.text: So glad you stopped in for a quick bite! Thank you for your business!

name: PandaMagicBooty
text: I'm amending my previous review of Ralph's because my most recent trip was fantastic. The wait was short, the food was delicious, and the staff was (and always is) friendly.

resp.text: Thank you for comments and your business.  Our apologizes for the faulty equipment it happens from time to time.  We are implementing new ideas to decrease wait time while serving the same great food. Please visit us again and thank you for your continued support of a family owned business.

name: William Gómez
text: Very delicious food and very friendly staff

resp.text: Thank you William for dining with us.  We are so glad you enjoyed your meal and so appreciate you taking the time to give us a review.  Customers such as you leaving a comment lets us know we are doing our jobs correctly.  It was a pleasure to serve you and hope to see you again soon.

name: jeremy irwin
text: These burgers are sooo good after a long day hiking the beautiful canyon! Made to order, and definitely worth the wait!! Corn nuggets and fried okra on point!

resp.text: The weather was perfect for hiking and we are so happy you finished your day with our burgers and sides! We look forward to seeing you again soon! Thank you for your business!

name: Pam Ogle
text: The BEST cheeseburgers in Fort Payne AL! And let’s not forget the AMAZING 1inch thick, light&fluffy pancakes for breakfast that are as big as the plate!!!! Great service too! Hands down my families FAVORITE restaurant for Breakfast, Lunch and Supper!

resp.text: Thank you so much! We are so glad you enjoy our burgers and pancakes! We appreciate your business and can’t wait to see you again soon!

name: Jeremy Moses
text: A must for a local burger. Great laid back atmosphere with excellent food and friendly service. If you are visiting little river canyon, make the day perfect by stopping at Ralph's.

resp.text: We appreciate your business! Thanks for stopping in!

name: Porkchopranch
text: Real good food no matter what you order. Service is very good and the prices are reasonable. Everything is fresh and served fresh. Great cheeseburgers and plate lunches.

resp.text: We appreciate your kind review. Thank you for your business!

name: Kenneth Blanchard
text: Staff was very nice and fun. I ate the large cheeseburger and it was definitely better than any gourmet burger I've had. I wish I lived closer. If you're on the area definitely stop in to eat. You won t be disappointed.

name: Scott Price
text: Love this place!! Great food and wonderful restaurants in store employees.

resp.text: Thank you Scott for your comment and support. We appreciate you and Susan and look forward to seeing you soon.

name: Clay Massengale
text: Non existent service.  Slow service was fine. I wasn’t in a hurry.  But after a 40 minute wait for a child’s cheeseburger we gave up and left.  Perhaps the four dollars they beat us out of will help them hire better employees.

resp.text: We apologize for the lack of service you experienced during your visit. During a busy weekend, we found ourselves short staffed and hope you will give us another try in the future.

name: Melanie Broome
text: AMAZING hippy burger this place hand makes the epitome of All burgers. yummmmm

resp.text: So glad you had the opportunity to dine with us and being courageous enough to try our Hippy Hole burger considering its size. Thanks so much hope to see you again soon.

name: Jason Druebert
text: Hands down the best burger in Northeast Alabama.

resp.text: Thank you Jason for taking the time to let us know how we are doing. Look forward to seeing you again.

name: Randy Williams
text: Great food always.

resp.text: Thanks Randy hope to serve you again soon.

name: Charles Curio
text:
Other guy was right, it was about 25/30 minutes and I was getting irritated...but the reply was right on..it was busy, but the food (burgers, Patty melt, fries) freaking awesome and worth the wait, hands down.
We'll come and wait, and eat again!

name: Jonathan Vance
text: Best place around!!!!!

resp.text: Thank you Jonathan we are so excited to hear from our customers. Guess it goes without saying especially when we got it exactly right for you. We appreciate your business and hope to serve you soon.

name: Richard Kuhn
text: Great place to grab breakfast, lunch, gas, or convenience items in between your little river canyon adventures. Great burgers. Clean and friendly.

name: Michael Shad
text: Very friendly staff and always good food. Best burgers within 25 miles.

resp.text: We appreciate your kind words! Thank you for your business, and we agree our burgers are the best!

name: Ron G
text: Best burgers on the mountain! Nice Lil quick stop for gas and camping supplies.

name: Lee Battles
text: Food like my Mawmaw used to make. Try it one time and check out the beautiful falls just next door.

resp.text: Within minutes from Little River Canyon and falls, we are glad you came in to visit! Come back and see us soon! Thanks!

name: J J
text: Great stop for great food!

resp.text: Thanks for stopping in! We appreciate your business and look forward to seeing you again soon!

name: Becky Payne
text: On our way to have breakfast here. A favorite place to visit each time we come to Ft. Payne!

resp.text: We appreciate you coming in to have breakfast with us! Thanks for your review!

name: Austin Rampey
text: Great spot.

resp.text: Thanks for coming in to see us! We appreciate your business!

name: Rickey White
text: Best meatloaf

resp.text: Thanks Rickey! We couldn’t agree with you more!!

name: cotton w
text: I will definitely be back

resp.text: Thank you for your business! Check out our daily lunch specials on our Facebook page!

name: Drew Cottrell
text: Very friendly staff and large selection of snacks before you go into little river falls

name: Bella Dennis
text: Good good nice people

resp.text: Thank you for your review! We love our team members too! We appreciate your business and hope to see you again soon!

name: Richard Hartline
text: Cheapest gas prices in Fort Payne.

name: luke lewis
text: DO NOT STOP HERE! Rest room was disgusting, and they charge high rates for products. They charged me over $2 just to put ice in my own water bottle.

name: Steve Spencer
text: Great place to get fuel friendly staff especially teresea she all ways has a smile on and very friendly stop by and tell her hi

name: Tyler Luthy
text: Clerk was sketchy accused me of loading my pockets. Bc I was checking energy drink shots bc half of the ones on the shelf we're 3 months or more expired. So I emptied my pockets on the counter and lifted my shirt as I was upset to be called a thief. And the clerk was like I'm one hell of a fighter let's go outside if you want too.. like what, no I'm here to buy something you jittery POS. Then he tried to charge me triple for the product. He was pathetic!

name: Kasey McKay
text: The website says its open.......it is NOT open during the hours it states it is, so if you are on the phone with your child who is low on gas and try to help them find a gas station just ignore this one.....because it might not be open.

name: John Smith
text: High quality gas, if I do say so myself.

name: Bobby Brown
text: Now I remember why I do not buy cigarettes from Mapco. The price is always wrong ex. The sign said $4.49 but the price is $4.96 and it said buy 2 save $0.50 but that is not true either. What else are they cheating us on?

name: Grant Dalton
text: Broken seal, this speaks for itself.

name: Nick Burgess
text: Mapco is a great place to come & get gas, get food w/ Mapco rewards u can't go wrong!!

name: Andy King
text: Hounded for money 4 times in 10 minutes. Saw them scare a young woman.

name: Dee Bail
text: Clean store, nice facility.

name: gerald Howard
text: The cashiers at this Mapco were the rudest and most unprofessional I have ever seen! Every single time I visit! Especially, the tall lady. She acts as if you're borrowing gas and not paying for it. Mapco Publix and Chick-fil-A are known for their courteous employees, but this location is tearing your name down!

resp.text: We apologize for the experience you described and we can assure you that behavior goes against our culture standards. We have alerted the District Manager over that location to take swift action.

name: Charity Shackelford
text: I would like to take this time to share a wonderful experience at this location. I purchased product at this particular location tonight. After my purchase I got in my car and was pulling out of the lot when a wonderful man by the name of Aaron came running to my car with my phone I had left on the counter. Thank you so very much for having such an honest and caring person on your team. Aaron you have no idea how much that meant. You saved so many photos/video's, all memories that I could never get back if it hadn't been for you. THANK YOU!

resp.text: Thank you for leaving such a nice review. We are glad that you loved our services, our dedicated staff will be pleased to learn of your high praise.

name: Mikie Morris (Mikie)
text: It was a few yrs ago that I had visited this establishment and being that Im from Colorado I was happy to find a fuel station in the area that sold diesel fuel. The cashier that night was more than helpful in answering a couple of questions for me. So I can't say anything bad about this place it was definitely a brighter note in my horrendous trip to the Huntsville area.

resp.text: Mikie, We are happy to hear you had a positive experience at MAPCO! We value your input and encourage you to let us know more details about your experience with us.

name: Debra Tarbox
text: Never have problems except when I come when it's busy. The staff are polite and that's even after dealing with disagreeable people. No matter where you go there are idiot drivers and people who think everyone owes them. Bless the staff who endure this corner of this side of town.

resp.text: Debra, Thank you again and it really helps to have customers like you sharing feedback regarding our performance.

name: Tiffany Wallace
text: The door was wide open when I went inside the store last night to buy drinks. I sat at the register for about 5 minutes with no one at the desk or even in the store. The lady behind me went out to the patio to find a cashier, and one came back in only to tell us they were closed. It was close to 4 AM, yet they say they're open for 24 hours.... Needless to say, I left the drinks I was planning to buy at the register and walked out. I'm not happy with their service at all.

resp.text:
Tiffany, We apologize for the experience you described and we can assure you that we have alerted the team of operations over that location to take swift action and resolve this matter.
Please allow us to earn back your trust.

name: Reese B
text: Don’t go here if you expect to do a quick stop. They usually have about 10 employees mingling around with one person takin cash. God bless you if they start chatting with the cashier because that’s going to tack on another 10 minutes to your trip

name: Jessie Basinger
text: Door was not set on automatic it was opened up 2". When we watched a local cop open the door by hand and go into the bathroom we followed. They told us...paying customers in uniform also (emergency road service crew) that only cops are allowed in right now... I suggest EVERYONE GO ACROSS THE STREET TO SUNOCO!! Very nice staff and actually open 24 hrs.

name: Daniel Yearta
text: I try to make sure I spend the least amount of my time & money here, as possible. It's one of those places that just want to appear to be clean on the outside but on the inside it's kinda disgusting. Workers attitudes toward customers are based on the color of your skin, normally only one cashier during busiest times of day, bathrooms are always atrocious and/or missing toilet paper/hand towels/soap, and most food is over or under cooked, if it's not already pre packaged and over priced. I only stop here if it's all that's open, if it's actually open, and in case of extreme emergencies. I avoid it like the plague! Enter at your own risk.

name: Victor Brant
text: 6:35am on 5/22/19 - Come in - Jessica says "HI". Get my coffee and start to head up to register. Again the store manager(tall black man) is behind the register. Jessica is at a register that has about 10+ customers in line. He calls for the next person in line. This goes on for a couple of minutes. I am next inline to be called "next", he looks up and see's who I am and he walks off!! With more than 10+ customers still in line to be helped! The customer in front of me finishes and Jessica greats me with a smile. "Good morning, did you see that", I asked Jessica. "Yes I did", she replied. This is the 3rd time this employee has provided very poor customer service, almost to the point that I am taking offence to it. I am thinking that Mapco is not going to do anything about it since nothing has happened.  It is a real shame that 1 employee can ruin your whole day and make your stores attitude not very pleasant to visit or deal with. I hope that you will take ahold of this comment and actually do something about it.

resp.text:
Victor, We apologize for the experience you described and we can assure you that behavior goes against our culture standards. We have alerted the District Manager over that location to take swift action and resolve this issue.
Please allow us to earn back your trust.

name: kitt Tidwell
text: Was about to make a $30 dollar purchase but was trying to find saltine crackers. My black boyfriend who was carrying the charcoal we were going to buy got approached by the cashier even though she had 5 people still in her line. She told him we were taking too long and needed to hurry up pay and leave. He went to the line after I gave up on my crackers and I went ahead to the side and asked her what the issue was. She just glared at me and wouldn't answer. I requested her the number of the manager, she gave me a fake number I found out later, and then told me I needed to leave or she would call the cops. My boyfriend and I deal with people against interracial couples all the time but this was absolutely disgusting to be treated this badly.

resp.text: Kit, We apologize for the experience you described and we can assure you that behavior goes against our culture standards. We have alerted the District Manager over that location to take swift action and resolve this problem.

name: Amanda Lynn
text: I'm not sure why everyone is giving such poor reviews. My husband and I happened to love this store. The staff and COFFEE are amazing. I'm horrible with names but the lady with red hair is a delight. There is long lines and most of the time there is no creamer in the machine and the coffee bar is dosgusting. But if people would clean up after themselves and do a little self help at the coffee bar, it would go a long ways ! You see the ladies checking all the customers out. We don't go anywhere else for gas or cigarettes.

resp.text: Amanda, Thank you so much for your review!

name: David Rieger
text: This store rarly ever has coffee  made at 1:30 a.m. I generallt gwve ro go to another store revery day for my coffee

resp.text:
David,  We have alerted the upper management  over that location so that they may resolve this issue.
Please allow us to earn back your trust.

name: J Allen
text: The coffee is #1 and the selection is GREAT! They're always busy and lines can get long but they make it up by the quickness and efficientcy of the employees, 2 - 3 minute wait tops!

resp.text: J, Thank you so much for your review!

name: Leah Heatherly
text: I am currently here at 3am this is a 24 hr store..... doors are wide open, and yet you come in just to get told they are closed. Sounds like ur paying your workers to do nothing!!!!! If ur not 24 hrs don’t advertise it

resp.text: Leah, We do apologize for the experience you have described. We can assure you we have notified the  team of operations regarding this situation to ensure this matter will be resolved.

name: Michael Odom
text: 99% of the time the parking lot is full of people loitering and panhandling. The restrooms are always a mess, full of flies, and understocked. There ALWAYS a line at the register, either because they're slow or too busy chatting with their friends.

resp.text: Michael, We apologize for the experience you have described. We do hope that you continue to be our guest at MAPCO and allow us to make your next visit a better experience.

name: J Goodwin
text: Went in to get coffee, a bite, & smokes but instead of getting served was told they was closed & wouldn't be open for another 30 mins when the sign on the door states plainly that they was open, some guy that doesn't even work there is the one whom relayed the message while the employee at the counter didn't even check up, I asked why the sign says 24 hours & his reply is that I could get gas at the pump with a card, there's a lot of gas stations that you can get gas at the pump after hours & they don't have a sign that says they're open for 24 hours cause that wouldn't be the truth, so why are y'all any different? I went to a different Mapco, they was open, & it wasn't 30 mins later. Your online hours also state that y'all are open 24 hrs, so I wasted gas, my time, & was lied to! If you look up Chevron that isn't 24hrs but can still get gas 24hrs hours with a card at the pump their store hours are correct, y'all should change your sign at the door & online to the correct service you provide.

resp.text: We apologize for the experience you described. We can assure you that behavior goes against our culture standards. We have alerted the Operational Leader over that location to take swift action.

name: Jeremy West
text: Consistent Mapco

resp.text: Thanks for placing your trust in us and your willingness to share. We always appreciate hearing back from our guest.

name: Terry Walker
text: I've just returned from this store. The syrup was out on the Coke fountain dispenser so I was only getting the carbonated water. A young man, his first day, understood the problem and relayed the message to another worker. I understand busy days, busy times, so I pulled out a chair and waiting. If ANYONE had acknowledged me at all - "sorry, ma'am, we haven't forgotten you" - but the other two employees wouldn't make eye contact with me at all. I'd be sitting there still waiting if they would've just acknowledged me. I hope a manager will review with them some proper customer service techniques. T

name: Taylor H
text: The worst gas station in the history of gas stations! Most pumps are out of order, card readers don't work, and employees are garbage.

resp.text: Taylor, We apologize for the experience you described and we can assure you this information will be passed on to  operations  over that location to take swift action and resolve this matter.

name: Rebecca Buckner
text: Ling waits inside for customers paying cash means credit / debit customers can't find an open pump while empty vehicles await their owner's return. Frustrating when you just want to get fuel and go.

name: draydre mccoy
text: My experience on 10/23/18... I went into the store tonight I only had change and a few dollars to get me some gas the cashier had a line of 7 people and was in the midst of having a conversation instead of waiting on customer when I finally got to the register I stepped beside the customer in front of me and began to count out my change the cashier in the store young black male with dreadlocks working the register seem to have a issue with me counting out my change because he had a lot of change in his drawer. I'm sorry sir but it's your job to count change. you're the one who chose the job of being a cashier in a gas station so you need to learn to deal with change. It's your job..

resp.text: Thank you for your feedback! I have forwarded this to the DM of this store to have investigated further

name: Rick Medal
text: Absolutely horrible place. Staff is completely rude and very SLOW. Homeless people and bummes everywhere.

name: Kimi Fletcher
text: I live within walking distance and have tried this location a few times out of convenience. Each time, the check out wait time is absolutely obsurd (about 8-12 min waits), slow-paced/undertrained staff struggle to keep lines down, and homeless people frequently panhandle INSIDE the store as well as outside.

name: Patrick Grijalva
text: I recently quit smoking so I'm thankful I won't be returning to this store, and I will make sure to get gas elsewhere as well.  The longest, most frustrating lines in town and other than a couple standouts,  the most annoyingly inept staff of all the Mapcos.  It seems to stem from poor management.

name: Kayla S
text: Easily the worst Mapco in Huntsville. Consistently understaffed with employees that have little to no understanding of customer service or money handling. This store is a black mark on Marco's brand. Its so bad even our law enforcement have stopped making this a rest stop. You will be here for 20 minutes if you need ANYTHING from a cashier. And if they run out of any change at all before you check out, they will take 10 minutes to restock their drawer instead of continuing to take customers and getting change as needed. Most employees will not ID for cigarettes until a manager is present. I don't think any of them have completed high school. All of them are rude as hell too. name: Brandon Young
text:
First off the guy sounded like he knew what he was doing so I gave him a chance on rebuilding my rearend. He told me that he can do it that all I needed to do is ordered the parts. So I did. So I called made an appointment to bring the truck down. Took it down on Thursday by Friday even it was done so I go pick it up. Everything seemed great going home then the following Sunday going to storage unit an all at once it felt like the brakes was grabbing and released but than I was hearing a noise. It happen so fast I made it to the road to pull off and got out to look. That's when I saw the rearend streaming hot. So I got someone to come get it to take it back. So I hauled it down and called the next day to let him know what happen. Had lots of people thats worked on them. Little farther away. They asked me what it done when it happen and they asked me how many pinion threads was showing so I counted and they was probably an 3/4 of an inch showing so they said that he over tightened it. Well the guy at South auto told me that it was a bad bearing in the kit that it would cost me another 200 or so dollars to be fixed so I've done been tho two different people rebuilding it. Put over $1000 in it already so therefore he wasn't holding his word either. So I just picked my truck up and told him I'll look at it myself bc I don't think it's much I hope. Well come to find out on my carrier bearings are hammer marks instand of pressing them on he used a hammer and beat them in so now Ive gotta put another set of bearing all the way tho the hole rearend. Costing another 100 dollars and free labor bc I'm doing it myself. Taking it apart and looking at it the outer pinion bearings is gone but worth me not driving it far I'm praying that I can clean everything up bc I'm not seeing alot of metal in it so hopefully it will be good after I get it fixed. JUST CANT TRUST ANYONE ON THEIR WORDS. Height not recommend anyone with rearend problems.

IF COULD POST PICS I WOULD OF THE MARKS.

CALLED AND NO ANSWERS SO HE MOST KNOW ITS ME CALLING.

name: Katheryn Young
text:
A Cup of Everything Convenience Store is truly convenient--a menu loaded with coffees, teas, and sandwiches primarily; and a medium-sized cache of snack bars, bottled and canned drinks, chips, and even things like headache medicine, this little restaurant/shop is a wonderful addition to the Square in downtown HSV. In addition to having just about anything you might find yourself needing while out on a stroll around downtown, or serving jury duty, etc., the staff is incredibly friendly and will (in my experience) go out of their way to ensure your good day.
However, you will be paying convenience store prices for most of their selections: a cup of coffee will only leave you a little better off than a visit to Starbucks (without the carefully constructed flavor--ACoE's coffee has been particularly bitter in my experience, even with sugar and cream), and the food can get a little pricey as well. Packaged foods, on the other hand, seem to be a bit cheaper than, say, the store inside the courthouse but it's not really enough to keep me from driving the little extra distance to the Publix at Twickenham Square.
The cozy atmosphere and neat meeting space upstairs, though, may be enough to counter-balance the slightly higher prices and not-so-awesome coffee--and a warm Spring day sat outside with a cold cup of iced tea and a fresh-made sandwich can't quite be beat.
So all-in-all, if you don't mind spending a bit more and not getting Starbucks-quality coffee, you will get a cozy, unique atmosphere great for a refreshing time on your own or with friends.

name: Karen Glenday
text: Always a wait! Too long. Pharmacy staff are like robots. Never thank you for shopping at Walgreens or even crack a smile. But yesterday was a serious violations. You require customers to wear masks inside the store. You have a sign posted outside reqiuring this. Several customers and including a cashier were not wearing their masks properly, not vovering their noses. I asked the male customer kindly to please wear his mask properly. He told me "to mind my own business and that I got up on the wrong side of the bed!" He was rude and self entitled. The cashier said nothing and wasn't wearing hers properly either. There were others as well. The cashier or someone should have asked them to either wear it properly or leave the store. This not happen. This is unacceptable during a pandemic. A pharmacy not enforcing their own rules. I believe much of this is politically motivated. Management and or any employee should report customers that do not wear masks covering the mouth AND nose should alert management immediately and tell them to wear it properly or leave the store. Personnel who do not wear masks properly should be fired or severely dealt with. Did any of these employees receive any training about the severity if COVID-19? Do they even care about not endangering their customers? Why should I ever enter that store again? All of this is unacceptable and not following CDC guidelines. This store is located in Fairhope, Alabama. I will report this to local health department authorities. I myself have been trained in contact tracing, epidemiology in public health, and spent my career in public and environmental health.

name: Sandy McDonald
text:
I've always had a very positive experience shopping at the Fairhope Ave. Walgreens.  The employees are always very nice and helpful, but my recent experience prompted me to take the time to write this review. I was looking for bar soap that contains zinc.

Katie, the young lady who assisted me went way above and beyond her duty to help me. While I was in the store, she looked in the store and online in an attempt to find the soap. When she found no immediate options, she asked that I call her in a few days so she could do some research. She found that zinc soap manufacturers are having production issues resulting in long backorder times, but that zinc supplements and sunscreen products were not impacted. She is now working with her manager to identify any special ordering options. I greatly appreciate Katie's kindness and genuine desire to help.

Second time something like this has something like this has happened  at this Walgreens.  Will not happen again.

They were not very helpful and somewhat annoyed when I asked them to please check with other local Walgreens. They were not busy at the time. I  was the only one there.

name: Page Ellis
text: Now that Walgreens has bought out the local Rite Aid, the pharmacy wait has become unacceptable. I gave it a few months to let them get acclimated to the larger number of customers but it has not improved. Last night it took 45 minutes to get my script which was called in by the doctor before hand. There were 10 people working behind the counter but it didn’t seem to make the process any faster. There must be something Walgreens can do to more efficiently process their customers in store. Walgreens, if you’re going to buy more customers from another pharmacy in an attempt to make more money faster, make sure you are able to keep the customers with good, efficient service. I also didn’t see the Rite Aid pharmacy employees who were supposed to be kept on staff when I came into the pharmacy this last time. I am missing the personal, friendly relationship with the employees and the good, quick service.

There was 2 of us, not a large party, so absolutely no excuse for not even acknowledging us. The food was good but that service had me irritated.

name: Wesley Thompson
text:
I come here on occasion for breakfast because as far as I know, this is the only place in town where I can get hash browns. I am including pictures of the breakfast and lunch menus.

The place is decked out with examples of Southern Americana and if a visitor wishes to see what life in the south was like decades ago, they can explore the museum, country store, and homestead that are located onsite.

Back to the food, though, because that's why I'm here today. I enjoyed a breakfast of two eggs, bacon, and hash browns along with toast and a bottomless glass of sweet tea. The bacon was a little undercooked today, but I like my bacon a little crisper than most, so everyone else would probably be okay with it. Other than that, everything else was spot on! Oh! Just a real quick PSA: be aware that if you get the pancakes they are plate sized and extremely filling. I messed up once and got the large order of them and could not finish them! Also, be patient as everything is cooked to order in the order in which it was received. It takes a bit longer to get your meal, but it is always hot and fresh.

Overall, Doc's is a wonderful little Mom and Pop place on the side of the road in a small South Alabama town - just the kind of place I like to visit when I'm on the road.

name: David Sims
text:
Was here on 8-12-16. Celeste took my order for a pizza at 4:41. I took a seat in a booth. Celeste apologized for the wait at 4:57. I said no big deal because I know that's not a long wait. However, at 5:11 I said ok guys it's been thirty minutes. How the pizza coming along? Celeste said its coming out now. I walked over to Bonnie and told her what pizza I was picking up and she was confused. Said she could make it. So after waiting thirty minutes my pizza hasn't even been prepped to go into the oven. I asked Celeste how to get in touch with the owner and she said she's new and doesn't even know the owner. Bonnie is just flat out lost. A woman named Margaret was there and showed no interest at all for my situation.
Here's why I'm so pissed. I'm a trucker and had started my ten hour break so I could leave at 2:30 the next morning. To get food, I had to restart my clock and drive to the next truckstop. I had problem with Bonnie last time I was there about six months ago because she skipped taking my food order to ring up items of people she knows. And I reminded her of that today. These three could screw up a two car funeral. No way if I owned this place would I leave it with these people!!!!!

text: There is not one employee in the building who is friendly, they all have attitudes, on the phone half the time, but have a sign up saying they won’t be rude and interrupt your conversation,

name: Scott Plagmann
text: Kind of a bit wild west after dark,beware!

name: Brandon Stone
text:
Update your shit.
Every pump had tape over the card reader.

name: Anthony Cornelius

name: Gabriel Pickett
text: Horrible service. This a dirty establishment. The cashier should wear gloves if you're going to service the community with nail fungus on your hands and touch food. Most of all don't pick customers, especially ones that visit this place daily before it became what it is today, to be rude too.

name: Susan Watkins
text: Customer service was average. Store kinda dirty, needed to be cleaned.

name: Curt Ryals
text: Walgreens pharmacy in general is horrible. Facility in Foley Al is twice as bad. Myself and wife have had to change do to the inability to provide a decent service. We’re sorry. Really busy. Come back tomorrow. We are having trouble with your ins. Same insurance the past 10 times I’ve been in. Automotive service says the Rx is ready. Drive to the window after an hour wait. We’re sorry, not sure what happened, can you come back in a couple hrs or maybe tomorrow. Same $&it every time. I would love to be contacted by someone at corporate. Horrible service and major attitude from the pharmacist at foley. It was all my fault in her eyes. Should be accustomed to it. I will now change my daughters Rx to a home town pharmacy.

name: Tammy Nance
text:
Great clean place with good service.
They carry all of grandpas favorite pipe tobacco.
Also has a Redbox.
Navigating the parking area can be tricky. Can be hazardous when busy.

name: Dwane Fresh
text: The only rd I use. Never had a bad experience there and have been going there for over 7 yrs!

name: Ellen Roberts
text: Drive thru was great

name: Richard Bailey
text: Doesn't enforce mask policy and closed drive through during pandemic.

name: becky kinder
text: Shelves are empty  because no one is coming to work!!  Stockroom filled with boxes to unload but no one comes to work...  Please.... Go to work so we can get back to normal....

name: Zach Rutledge
text: A good selection and clean, but expensive even with loyalty card discounts.

name: Jess Mason
text: I  love how they have a little bit of everything it makes shopping easier!

name: Kandi Winters
text: Script completed correctly and in time. Nice people.

name: kathy Farris
text: Excellent service with a smile here, with NO wait...thank you to Jennah for her compassion and understanding..

name: Melissa Grace
text: Went to drop off my mother's prescription and the lines were backed up down an aisle. There had to be 20 people just standing around the pharmacy area & suddenly two customers begin yelling, cussing & threatening each other. Several customers asked a Walgreens employ to call the police, & she decides to page just management. At this point I walked out & told my 74 yr old mother NEVER to go back there. The parking lot is dangerous too!

name: Ed Wheeler
text: We use the pharmacy and always have found them polite and knowledgeable. There phone notification is timely. When an item is not in stock they have always gotten it withing 24 hours.

name: jane .flippo
text: Sick baby’s prescription called in from doctor office at 9:30 am. Mom went to pick it up at 4; not ready. Pushed out of line by window clerk with no explanation. I returned at 7:30 pm, waited in line 18 minutes to find out is still not ready! Asked for insurance card, it’s on file for a regular prescription. Took 20 more minutes to be ready. Asked why, got a shoulder shrug! Asked someone else why, got an “I don’t know...” Store manager not in. Now brick baby has missed 3 doses of prescription and not one person can tell me why, apologize, or offer a Refund! Go to a Publix! Don’t waste your time here!

name: Roxanne Dugger
text: When I stayed in Spanish fort I loved going to Walgreens, but for whatever reason every time I try to get a prescription from the one in Foley I have to fight to get it done. For one thing they don't let me know when it's ready. My most recent prescription they tried to say my insurance would only cover but one pill. That's bull because first of all it's not even expensive without insurance, second, I have BCBS and my package is over 500 a month so it's not some rinky dink insurance. Just save yourself some trouble and go to island drug. I have never had an issue, and they treat me like I'm a friend not a number.

name: Brandy Knodel
text: I stood in line for almost 25 minutes when I got up to the counter the girl pulled out two of the three prescriptions and then instead of asking me to wait or even telling me anything she looked past me and called for the next customer. Not once saying anything until I asked her what I was supposed to do.  While I understand that they were indeed busy,  there is no reason for rudeness. Shame on Wendy!

name: Boxcar Willy
text: Great store - Always clean and staffed good - Pharmacy is the greatest!  Always on their game and always friendly and helpful! Best pharmicist on the coast!!! We love this store!

name: Andrew Novak
text:
Guaranteed the biggest groups of idiots you will find in one space

*UPDATE*
It has been 10 months and Walgreens has failed to fix or provide any feedback to any of their high number of 1 Star reviews (more 1 stars than any rating put together as of 3/13/19) glad to know how much they actually care about their business. Just go to publix trust me

name: Rhonda Puryear
text: Great place to find excellent deals.

name: Dorothy Brown
text: I would give this pharmacy zero stars if I could. They do not value your time at all. I went to pick up a prescription for my dad from the weekend & it wasn't ready. It was a partial prescription so it should have been ready. They knew I was waiting but they didn't care. Everyone else who was waiting came & gone. I sat there 30 minutes. This pharmacy is a joke.

name: Amy Hale
text: The pharmacy Staff at the window is always rude! There is no need in being rude to anyone especially someone who is sick. If you don’t like your job get another one preferably not in a customer service field.

name: NOOB_ FPV (NOOB_FPV)
text: Horrible place to fill prescriptions!  Rude and unprofessional. Ridiculous really that you can’t speak to a person who’s job is to serve without being short and disrespectful and have an attitude.  I understand a bad day but this isn’t the first time and by the remarks I see below combined with a very low rating, it’s easy to see why.

name: Bridget L
text: The pharmacist was very helpful and nice.

name: Anna Gonzalez
text: 4 months pregnant wearing a heart monitor, I called to see if my 4yo ADHD medication was in stock before I drove all the way there with my 2 other children. They told me they couldnt tell me over the phone they would have to see the prescription to answer that! Drove up there had to take my kids out and go in, my sick 2 yo in my arms asleep and ofcourse they didnt have it, I wasnt rude I asked why they couldn't of told me before they said because of the type of medication its an requirement I asked of it was a law and no its not a law its only a precautionary requirement, my son has multiple special needs not just ADHD and with a history at this pharmacy you would think a simple yes or no could of happened. Not coming back, it's sad I get better service and hospitality at Walmart.

name: d Busch
text: The pharmacists are patience and kind.

name: Denise Dixon
text: My son has asthma and was in need of his medication as soon as possible i went through and refilled his prescription at 12:30 and was told to come at 2 to pick up.. i get off work early to pick up his meds only to be told they " somehow got pushed back" and that it will be a few hours now. This is the most UNPROFESSIONAL AND UNORGANIZED PHARMACY i have ever did business with. I will no longer do business with this pharmacy!!! They should be SHUT DOWN how they run this pharmacy especially since it is someone's MEDICATION!!

name: Amanda W
text: Very rude staff. Perhaps they should find a new line of work, away from the public.

name: Aunyea Edwards
text: This store is horrible. They are the biggest group of idiots one will ever find. I talked to 3 different people whom all had the I.Q. of a doughnut. They couldn't tell me anything about my rx, customer service is nonexistent at this store. Then the dumbest one that answered the phone complained to me how she been answering calls all day, I told her good job you're at work that's what you're suppose to do. I swear this Walgreens was sent from hell to drive all their customers away.   If you need a rx, just drive somewhere else anywhere else. These people will have you on hold all to day just to not resolve your issue. I wish I could subtract these damn stars.

name: Hillary Baxter Hopper
text: I tried dropping off a fedex package and had, what I'm assuming was the manager(Brown curly hair), tell me over and over again that I was wrong and it was not Fedex. I left the store feeling very small and extremely disrespected. I knew I was in the right and having someone speak to me that was so insulting. I went straight my usual Fedex drop off who gladly took my package.

name: Sheri Dorgan
text:
FOLEY ALABAMA Between Happy & RUDE.........
I called Wal green's in Foley, Al. to ask how much my husband's prescription was. The pharmacist answered the phone and I ask the price of the medication. He replied in a condescending monotone “he is over the age of 18 and he can call himself” I said “excuse me” and he repeated himself.  I am calling corporate in Deerfield IL., first thing in the morning. It is bad enough to be sick, but to have a pious demoralizing pharmacist talk down to you when you are giving them your hard earned money is just not the norm……. He acted like he had done a few dowers himself.

name: Kimberly Hinman
text: Horrible customer service. Inflated prices and the store manager has absolutely no idea what she is doing. The pharmacy techs are rude and I waited in line for over 28 minutes. Go to Walmart instead!

name: The Band
text: we are lucky to have convenience of nation wide pharmacies in foley. i was feeling under the weather due to low thyroid. my provider in california filled it and we got it transfered. they sell lots of diabetes self testing supplies at this walgreens. its a mystery why all walgreens cvs stores arent cookie cutter identical

name: Bryan Byl

I asked if they would transfer mine to Walmart they said they are not able to do that!! I have had it done a few times before! Ugh I will not recommend them to anyone!

name: Brenda Lemus
text: The clerks at the pharmacy are rude and mean I just wanted to ask one a question about my medication and she started having a damn attitude with me.If they not  gonna be nice they should not be working there.I recommend you not going there if you do not have time because they take a long time just to give a medicine!

So i put it in my car and didnt open the box until i got home. And it wasnt the same one. It already had juice in it and dirty crud in the holes in it. So i carried it back and they refused to give us anything in return and told us to leave. . I suggest yall dont do business with very rude and unrespectable people. I f i could have gave them 0 stars i would have.

text: Literally the one Stop store for everything. All the way from fine wine, to tanning beds! Fresh food cooked daily, super awesome workers, great line of CBD and vape equipment, just all around amazing!

resp.text: Awesome glad to have u as a loyal customer

name: Op Zorb
text: A nice store with everything you need. From good to house hold items. A great little liqueur store with fair prices. Friendly staff.

name: Penny Lightsey

name: Mariah Cassels
text: Great prices, good pizza & a good selection of food, household needs & great vape & juice prices!

name: Hina Patel

text: You mess with 1 truck driver you mess with all of us, don't go there just keep driving.

name: Roman Harrell
text: Super slow pharmacy. Avoid this place unless you have 45 minutes to even drop off a prescription and then have to come back and wait another 45 minutes in-line to pick it up. They have two registers but only use one and they are not in a hurry at all.

name: Shelly Byrne
text: I went through the drive thru last night to pick up flu meds. The one the doctor recommended was going to cost me $60, but then the precious lady at the window told us we could get a coupon online that would make the medicine only $30 instead. By the time I had it pulled up on my phone, she had my prescription ready. Thank you so much! (Wish I had gotten the lady’s name!)

name: Andrew Rolfsen
text:
AVOID THIS LOCATION

Since covid hit this store has become more and more poorly managed. The customer service is abysmal at best. My last visit this week I pulled into the drive through and waited 48 minutes for the six cars ahead of me to be serviced. Forty....eight.....minutes. 6 customers serviced in FORTY EIGHT MINUTES. And you know what I was told? Despite getting a text at 1138 that morning saying my prescription was ready, they couldn't find it. So I waited 48 minutes to NOT GET MY FREAKING PRESCRIPTION. and no. You can't just leave the line. Its physically impossible to do so once trapped in. Thats it. Im done. I've had all my prescriptions transferred to Adam's across the street.

AVOID THIS LOCATION

name: Tony Roberts
text: This is the worst Walgreens I have ever been too!There service is very unorganized. The drive thru is slow and they never answer the phone!

name: sunny love
text: This Walgreens deserves zero stars. The pharmacy personnel is rude and unprofessional.  I have spent over a week trying to be reimbursed the money that they overcharged my debit card when they triple charged me for one prescription.  Even the Walgreens CSR I spoke with said she was filing a complaint because they were extremely rude to her.

name: Jamie Norris
text: Is there a way to leave negative stars? The pharmacy is absolutely the worst. The drive through is a single lane and once you’re in line, there is no getting out. For the third month in a row I have waited nearly 45 minutes to an hour to get my Rx and the inside is just as bad. We always seem to be a horrible inconvenience to them and my husband and I have decided that it’s just time to switch pharmacies all together.

name: Brianna Lamb
text: I came in to see family in Alabama and got sick and needed some meds filled while I was down here. I waited for over an hour, and even asked twice when my prescription would be ready. I was told, “it’s almost ready. Give us just a few more minutes.” The lady who rung me out acted like I was bothering her and distracting her from doing her inventory. She didn’t even have the decency to look up at me while checking out. If there was anyway to put negative stars, I would. When I’m on vacation, I hoped to be able to trust a pharmacy. That was not the case here.

name: Jessica Joyner
text: Dropped off a class II prescription yesterday and was told that they would check to see if the item was in stock once the pharmacist returned from lunch. Pharmacy technician even verified my phone number. 2 hours later, I came back to pick up the prescription and I could not go through the drive-thru due to 18-wheeler blocking it. Parked car and went into the store and waited in line only to be told they didn't have the medicine in stock. They didn't even have the common decency to call and let me know so I didn't waste 2 hours of my time. 😒

name: Heidi Smith
text: Yesterday ( saturday) all pharmacists called in...so no meds. Now been in line an hour on Sunday. Awful service. Rude employees

name: Ricky Pyles
text: Usually a nice visit. The pharmacy ppl can be a little rude. I've stood at the counter on several visits as they carry on personal conversations instead of tending to customers as they come up.

name: Molly Lowery
text: The pharmacy is horrible, as is usual for Walgreens. I waited 40 minutes to pick up my medicine only to be told they put it back on the shelf because it had been 12 days since the script was called in. No one called to make sure I would still get it or anything. Like most people, I stay busy and haven’t had time to go by - the line is always really long inside and at the drive thru. They’ve lost my business.

name: Eric Reda
text: Very friendly and engaged sales floor team (for the most part, and the leadership team is relatively swift at removing anyone not fit for a customer service position) and the store stays in stock, clean, and organized -  the GM hasn't changed in over a decade so he's clearly doing something right. As with any Walgreens, the pharmacy staff is my biggest complaint; that's depending on who you talk to of course. They're not ALL rude, unhelpful, and work at a snail's pace. Regardless, all it takes is that one "bad apple"  to ruin the customer's experience - hence the 4/5 rating.

name: Jen Cazer
text: The young girl at the pharmacy counter acted as if I discussed her when I tried to ask about a tetanus shot, not once but twice she made us feel as if we were bothering her on her day off, I've never been treated so rudely in a place of business.... & I used to love the place.

name: Latrisha Brown
text: Rude and unprofessional. Every time I call their system is down. Half of the time, they don’t answer the phone! I will be transferring to a different pharmacist.

name: D Nelson
text: Switched to this location recently, and I am pleased with my interactions with the pharmacy staff (prompt and polite while being efficient) and special thanks to Crissy/Crystal(?) in Photo department. She was extremely helpful, patient, and knowledgeable!

name: Stephanie Carroll
text: I got my wedding invitations here. They helped me alot! My invitations are exactly like I wanted them. I'm so thankful for them. Will definitely be using them again!! Beucana and a guy helped us  and they were so sweet and very patient with me so if you need pictures printed I suggest Walgreens there amazing!!!!

name: Rebecca Rolling
text: LOVE the original pharmacy staff under Pharmacist Barry Brewer...professional, friendly,helpful staff but when Rite Aid merged they brought the rude folks with them..Melissa Evans is a Gem!

name: Helen Taylor
text: Hayden was very helpful when I called to see if an item was in stock.

name: No Clue
text: It’s a fine Walgreens waits can be up to 40 minutes at max.

name: Jessica Lucas
text: I'd long written off ever getting my medications from a Walgreen's after years of getting terrible, slow, and rude service, but today was a wholly different experience. My prescriptions were ready by the time I arrived there coming from the doctor's office, everyone was friendly, and it was a great shopping trip despite my illness. Thanks!

name: Colby Johnson
text: The absolute slowest, most care free staff that I’ve ever seen. When you are in pain and need to pick up your prescription, run far away from here.

name: Vanessa Brown
text: They can be extremely slow at times. However, they are always very friendly as well as helpful. I've been looking for various items before, that they didn't carry, and they are happy to tell you were to go nearby to find it. I've also found some really cute and cheap tunics at this location.

name: Lyndsay Rohan
text: I injured my shoulder and pulled up to the drive thru at 9:58pm. The pharmacy closes at 10. The tech said there wasn’t enough time to fill my prescription, but ended up telling me to hold on. The pharmacist came to the window and told me he’d get me taken care of. I’m so thankful for him !!!

name: Lindsey Brown
text: Have gone here for years for mine and my family's prescriptions, as well as quick pick up items. I wanna say that have treated us right more often times than not. The times that they might have overstepped was when they were equally as frustrated as I was. TBH I love their rewards program and app even synced to it my step counter. Now I'm getting rewards points and not spending a dime :D. Just try to remember to avoid their busiest hours.

name: ED KILLGORE
text: Slow! Slow! Slow! I am a full-time RVer so in my travels I have occasion to use Walgreens in different areas. They need to tighten up and get with the program. Their pharmacies are poorly managed. What's the point in busily filling pill bottles if you don't wait on the customers who are waiting in line to pick up their prescriptions. I wish Rite Aid hadn't sold out to them. I will be taking my business to CVS.

name: Sandra Love
text: Repeated rudeness from young pharmacist. They think they are the only hardworking people around. The ladies on the floor are mostly nice but lm changing pharmacies as soon as possible

name: Back To My ROOTS
text:
The absolutely slowest drive through of any establishment that I have ever endured. To make mattrrs worse, single lane so once you are in line, you are trapped.

A few other: They take so long to contact your Dr. For refills. I dropped a script but was 3 days early. They told me what day to come back and when I showed...they had lost the script. I had to go back to my mother's Dr. to get a replacement. Even worse, they acted like I never even dropped off the first one.

name: Kristeena Anderson
text: Pharmacist is not friendly and they are extremely slow to get your precriptions.

name: TT
text: Used for Years great pharmacy

name: Gary Hill
text: Horrible beyond belief!! Don’t even deserve 1 star! Do not go here! Go to Millbrook, it’s a night and day difference. My script has been lost multiple times, once was given someone else’s medication. Waited for someone to  acknowledge me for 5 minutes once, but I did get to over hear the technician on a personal phone call talking to someone about smoking weed so that was entertaining while I waited. It’s unbelievable that these people are allowed to assist in someone’s wellbeing!

name: Brady Galloway
text: I can just walk right in and buy a Baby Ruth bar! There is also a Redbox here. The inside just like any other Walgreens, nice.

name: Shari Belcher
text: Horrible experience! I was placed on hold for nearly 10 minutes. The phone rang back 3 times and no one ever came to the phone. As a matter of fact when I said hello, someone sent me back to more music. I spoke to Shay the pharmacist and this is normal practice for them. I went to Publix instead!!! I can only think that people go to this location out of habit. However, I’d rather spend my money where I am respected as a customer.

name: Fay Elliott
text: Has everything I need that is free of dyes and perfume for my rare skin cancer. I would have given 5 stars but they need to hire more employees since CVS isn't on Express Script recommendation now and are getting longer lines meaning longer waiting times in the pharmacy.

name: Amber Nicole
text:
Love coming here for my RX and sweets needs 😊
Pharmacy usually does good at getting you in and out.

name: Sidney Watson
text: Love using them for my prescriptions. Drive thru is super convenient.

name: John Hines (Wareagle_81)
text: Great customer service. Always friendly and respectful. A little slow due to high cutomer traffic but thats to be expected when you the best in town. Great job s.mememorial walgreens. Of Prattville.

name: Cayman Goodwine
text: Extremely rude, lost multiple prescriptions of mine. Never been to a Walgreens this slow. Do not come here! I will not be back.

name: Jacob Quimby
text: I mostly go to Walgreens for their Walgreens exclusive Funko Pop toys, that my son and I collect, and this store doesnt even get half of the ones that come out. Walgreens doesnt usually sell them on the website, and the closest store that does have them is completely out of my way, and a chore for me to get to. Ive honestly never purchased anything else from this store, but the staff have always been friendly and the store is clean and well organized.

name: Pine Mountain Chalet 108
text: Horrible place for prescriptions!  Be prepared to spend your day,  night and next morning waiting in line and don't even attempt the drive through!

name: Rachel Moore
text: Love the store, but pharmacy not so much.

name: Ricardo Rodriquez
text: WOST possible place to get meds! I will NEVER to business at this location ever again. I went to publix to get some prescription eye drops within 2 minutes they told me they were unavailable to fill it. I decided to go to Walgreens. I dropped off the prescription she looked at it and said it would take 2 hours. I got an automated call half an hour later saying it would be delayed and THEY WOULD contact me once my prescription was ready. I waited an hour and a half and called them. Thats when they tell me they couldnt fill my prescription. I asked why did i have to wait 2 hrs in pain when publix told me they couldnt fill it within 3 minutes.

name: Doug Tate
text: I trust this Walgreen with all my precriptions . They send out text alerts to me when the medicine is ready and when the preccription is done.

name: Tony Johnson
text: Store is clean, well stocked and the employees are very helpful.  A+

name: Michael Smith
text: Very judge mental, unprofessional pharmacy. A family member brought a prescription into this suppose to be professional pharmacy and they REFUSED to fill her medication. For whatever reasons they believed the medication was prescribed for, it was none of their business. The pharmacist asked her personal questions regarding why she was prescribed the medicines. I think that this was appalling and disrespectful to this young lady. What kind of business is this to pick and choose what medications to fill for a patient? If you are a licensed professional who people rely on for medical advice/ or information, then you are clearly in the wrong profession if everything is based off of your personal feelings or opinion.

name: J. Cope
text: The young woman in the 𝐏𝐡𝐚𝐫𝐦𝐚𝐜𝐲 is very rude and frankly, I don’t think she knows what she’s doing. It is EXTREMELY OBVIOUS she doesn’t like her job! I won’t go back because of her.

name: Karen Cooper

Should have signs posted because I'd have definately gone on down the road and spent my money somewhere else if I'd known.

Instead of talking to your friend why don't you go fix it.  In the day of covid I shouldn't have to go inside when the employee and her friend don't have thier face covered.

Sign outside says that they stay open 24/7, but that's a lie.
Stopped by one night after I got off work to pick up some things, only to find that they were closed. Went in the following morning and asked an employee why and apparently they only stay open until midnight because the manager wants to "save money".
What good is a CVS store if its not open 24 hours??? I'll just go to the publix literally next door during regular daytime hours if that's the case.
I hope you idiots go out of business.

In addition, I was given a generic from Aurobindo Pharma which is a pharma being cited by the USFDA for quality violations. Aurobindo has recalled 80 lots of medicine, not mine particularly, but who wants to risk that? CVS should stop filling medications from that company, period.

text: Great place to visit for all of your tobacco needs, vape/juices, mods, U,-Haul, and all sorts of interesting items. You would usually just run into your local convenient store for just your usual pack of cigs, but with this store, you'll catch yourself somehow checking out the hats, shirts, jewelry, and everything else in between. I have been a long time customer (approx. 6-8yrs) of the Discount Tobacco store and I must say the customer service/cashier whose name is Nicole is amazingly nice and respectful. When it was just her and Smokey running the store,  those times were great and service was always 5 Stars, most definitely than any other store within this county. With Smokey no longer working there, I just hope they keep Nicole there because it wouldn't be the same without either 1 of them. I see them both as the backbone of this business and the reason it's as successful as it is today. With all of that being said, I highly recommend this Tobacco store to anyone looking for great deals on products along with being treated respectfully as a customer.

text:
I haven’t been treated with customer service when getting my prescriptions filled. I have a few complaints.
1. I was shorted on medication and another time I was given more.
2. My 1st inhaler prescription, when I got it home I seen on the sheet something to the effect of “demonstrate to first time users” which the pharmacist did not do. I actually had to google how to use it and watch you tube videos.
3. What topped the cake today was I recieved a text message 3 days ago from cvs saying my prescription was ready and I had 8 days to get it before it was returned. Today when I went to pick it up, they told me it was not ready. I asked how long it was going to take and told her I didn’t plan on coming back out today. She said I had to wait 45 minutes or come in and it may be shorter. I left and came back 15 min to ask for the corporate number and the manager’s name. The manager comes to the window with my prescription and says it’s ready. I explained to her my other two concerns above and how I feel mistreated (or not treated the same way how I see them treat other customers-I don’t want to throw the race card) but, she ultimately throws my meds down and walk away.

I’ve called the corporate number, hopefully I hear something back.

name: Bill Rice
text: They took advantage of my teenage son.  The pump handle stuck and wouldn't stop after the tank filled.  He ran to get them to shut off the pump after getting gas all over his clothes.  This was clearly a problem with the pump as they constantly are having problems at this location.  Then they blamed him and charged him nearly $40 for all the gas that was pumped.  When I returned an hour later to ask for a refund, all of the pumps were shut off, as shown in the pictures, because they had another problem.  They refused a refund, refused to look at video to show that my car savvy son did nothing that could cause this problem, and forwarded my info to another manager.  Bottom line:  the gas price may be cheap but they are crooked, disrespectful, and refuse to admit the pumps are broken.  I'm looking forward to the opening of a Kroger gas station just down 72.

text:
Sat, Mar 12, Madison, AL corner of County Line and Hwy 72, store 8897
Did enjoy this Mapco since its opening due to convenience. However, today multiple pumps weren't operational, and three different keypads weren't functioning forcing us to move around an already busy station.  We settled on one that flowed very slow.  A young lady beside us was charged before $.01 before the pump shut down.  We walked in to let the attendant behind the counter know, and he said nothing while shrugging his shoulders, twice, and proceeded to ignore us.  Mapco should be ashamed of not only allowing a relatively still new station, in a busy spot, to be so inadequate, but also for hiring such a poor excuse for customer service.  We'll be finding another station, which is also disappointing because this one was convenient.  Boo!!!

The older ladies are always nice and polite and though I could understand if it was sporadic visits during the week but it's literally everyday that I come for breakfast and lunch. They have great coffee the best I've found in Cullman. Again though the attitudes have made my visits undesirable and I'll be going there less now.  Another example has been when I get wings or chicken strips or even a hamburger they dont ask if I want condiments that generally go with the food but they will ask everyone around me if they want sauce or lettuce and tomato??? I am in Cullman for work purposes and when I found this place it was like a little hole from home and I fell in love but that has since deteriorated a bit and will be visiting less. :(

name: Holly Stemmler
text: Dear Marathon on 231 north in Midland city Alabama, that was dirty. Your store hours posted clearly say you are open until 8:00 pm on Sunday. Google says the same thing. You had more than one customer try to open the door and proceeded to shut the lights out. ALL OF THEM. INSIDE AND OUT! With people standing at the door! I understand having closing work to do but that was BEYOND rude. I called your store. You answered "Marathon" and when asked why you closed an hour early your reply was "honey, this is a residence. They don't have a phone there anymore. Sorry." And then you hung up on me. I don't appreciate being hung up on for one and for two, don't call me honey. I will find a way to contact a manager tomorrow if I have to start at cooperate and work my way down. I hope you sleep well tonight knowing you left people standing in the pitch black DARK. I will be absolutely sure to let every single person I know (which is QUITE a many) to keep driving up the road to the Shell where you aren't treated like a nuisance.

text: I went to this Walgreens to drop off a Fedex package and the cashier at the front of the store was friendly and helpful however the lady in the photo department in charge of receiving packages was rude and didn’t want to help. She told me “she didn’t have any space left to hold my package” and then ended up taking the package anyways after she sighed and reluctantly took it. I told her thanks for the help and she just mumbled “mhm” while not looking at me at all and just walked off. Not a very good employee.

name: Suresh Mathews
text: Driver’s beware: This is a review for the Drive-through pharmacy pick-up. Friendly staff at the window; fairly quick service. If paying by cash the change is returned in an envelope - all great. But, drivers beware of your car/SUV driver’s side tire scraping the sides of the concrete. It happened to me couple times, and the second time was scary loud that I thought my tire ripped. Fortunately, it was fine. The exit out of the drive through is narrow and curves left; and therefore the tire scraping the concrete. It appears that this happens to every driver that is unaware of the lurking danger. I called and made a complaint with the Manager but there have been en changes yet to the drive through. I’ve educated myself that i need to turn my wheel to the right as I exit out and then lean left into the turn. This way the driver’s side rear wheel gets more space and avoids scraping the concrete.

They were also incredibly rude and not helpful AT ALL. It's not like Walgreens doesn't carry this medication either, as I've been able to purchase it at other Walgreens locations in the past, and it is a prescription medication.

But I took it to Walmart and they had no issues filling it. The 2nd run in was after i had surgery and the tech was extremely rude. I asked what the hold up was, thinking they may need to see my license or insurance and he responded "there isn't a hold up i told you it would be 15 minutes and it hasn't been." Then this last time they were going to charge me $194 for a monthly prescription,  I told them I couldn't afford that and had the dr call me in the same prescription to CVS, it was $0 and covered fully by my insurance. Will not go back.

text: I have only ever used the drive thru. My experience there varies. At times, I feel valued and am cheerily greeted by an employee who seems to genuinely care and enjoy their job. Other times, I am not greeted at all for several minutes while the employee types away on their computer (more than one of the employees do this). It’s not hard to quickly pick up the drive thru line and say “Welcome, I’ll be with you in just a moment” and carry on. As a customer, it does not leave a good impression when you are neglected. Typically the wait time is incredibly long, even if my prescription is filled and ready to go. I will continue to use this Walgreens because my insurance switched its contract from CVS and it is the closest location to me. But I will advise my friends and family against going here. The employees here need reinforced training on customer interaction.
